title: salsa
directions: Put peppers into shallow dish and add water to just cover them.

Microwave peppers for about 1 min. Chop in half and put in blender. Add onion, garlic, cilantro, salt and juice from the canned tomatoes. Blend until it forms a slightly chunky mixture. Add whole tomatoes to the blender. Pulse the blender 4 or 5 times or until the sauce reaches the desired consistency. Grab a bowl of chips and enjoy!

title: squash parmesan
directions: Clean and slice squash and cook until tender, about 10 minutes or less and drain.
Drain a little juice from tomatoes.
Stir gradually into flour to make a thin paste.
Stir that back into rest of tomatoes.
Add sugar and seasonings into tomatoes.
Grease 2-quart casserole; alternate squash, Mozzarella cheese, tomatoes and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350° or microwave 10 to 15 minutes, turning twice.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix butter, chocolate, sugar and milk.
Boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off heat.
Add tidbits and stir until melted.
Add Marshmallow Whip and stir until well mixed.
Add nuts, if desired, and pour onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: 5 cup fruit ambrosia
directions: All fruits from cans.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans down.
While beans cook, saute onion in oleo. Drain beans; add onion, cheese and soup.
Place in greased casserole.
Crumble crackers into remaining oleo until absorbed. Sprinkle crumbs on top of casserole and bake at 350° until brown.

title: japanese pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine with sugar and eggs.
Fold in pecans, coconut, raisins and vinegar.
Will make 2 pies.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco together until light and fluffy.
Then add butter.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Next add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in large mixing bowl until this is very light.
Slowly add milk and flour, ending with flour.
Then add vanilla.
Bake 2 hours in 300° oven in a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
It is better to have ingredients at room temperature.

title: greek salad
directions: Chop lettuce and tomatoes.
Mix with peppers, olives, oregano, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in oil and toss.
Garnish salad with rounds of onions on top.

title: scalloped cabbage #2
directions: Combine water, salt and sugar; add cabbage.
Cook about 4 minutes (do not overcook); drain.
Place cabbage in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix margarine, flour and milk and cook until thick. Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over cabbage. Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: orange whip
directions: Stir and refrigerate.
To make strawberry Julius, omit orange juice and substitute a 10 ounce package of frozen strawberry puree.

title: squash dressing
directions: Melt butter.
Mix cream of chicken and add other ingredients, one at a time.
Mix well and bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt butter with onion.
Place all other ingredients with butter and onion.
Pour over broccoli. Bake in baking dish at 400° until brown, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes, then baste meat.

title: date bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Let stand until cool.
Combine butter, sugar and date mix.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to other ingredients.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden toothpick thrust into center comes out clean.

title: spanish hamburg
directions: Mix together hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, milk, salt, and pepper.
Form into patties.
Brown on both sides in skillet. Combine catsup, water, vinegar, sugar, and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over hamburger.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in the water;
work in enough flour for a light dough.
The less flour the softer the cookie.

title: pork steak and sauerkraut
directions: Makes an easy meal with baked potatoes, pork and beans.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Beat until fluffy.
Put vanilla wafer in cupcake holder.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 370° for 20 minutes.
Top with favorite topping and add whipping cream.
Makes about 24 cupcakes.

title: vanilla wafer roll
directions: Soak gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water; add to beaten egg yolks and sugar.
Cook in double boiler until thick and smooth; cool. Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Crush wafers with rolling pin.
Place a layer of crumbs in a well-greased loaf pan.
Pour over a layer of filling.
Repeat, making 5 layers.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: pralines
directions: Mix and cook sugar, milk and Karo until soft ball forms in glass of water.
Take off fire and stir, then add oleo and stir. Add pecans until thick.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let stand until hard.

title: easy home bread
directions: Place yeast in 1 cup of warm water with 2 tablespoons of the sugar.
Then add second cup of water.
Then stir in egg, sugar and salt.
Next blend in flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition. Finally stir in oil slowly and mix.
Cover and let double in bulk (about 1 hour), punch down.
Put into loaf pans and let rise an hour or double.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn oven up to 425° to brown.

title: enchiladas
directions: In 8-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, fry tortillas one at a time 2 to 3 seconds on each side.
Drain tortillas on paper towels.
(You may omit this step, if desired.)
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of hot oil into 10-inch skillet.
Over medium heat, in the 2 tablespoons oil, cook onion and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup, meat, water, cumin and green chilies.
Heat thoroughly.
Spoon about 1/3 cup soup mixture onto each tortilla; roll up.
Arrange filled tortillas in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour taco sauce evenly over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Uncover; bake 5 more minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: christmas trees
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Pour over cereal in large bowl; mix to coat.
Shape warm mixture 2/3 cup at a time into Christmas trees on waxed paper with buttered hands.
Decorate with gumdrops to represent tree ornaments; add paper stars for tops.
Let stand until cool. Yield;
3 dozen.

title: one pot chop supper
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add other ingredients. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: hot rolls(plain flour)
directions: Mix and heat milk, sugar, salt and lard nearly to boiling. Let cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast cake.
Work in flour; set to rise.
Grease bowl.
Cool 2 hours in warm weather.
Pour back out and make out in rolls or biscuits.
Let set to rise.
Make small rolls.
Bake at 325°.

title: punch bowl cake dessert
directions: Layer in a large glass bowl in the following order: cake pieces, pudding, Cool Whip and candy pieces.
Repeat until there are 2 or 3 layers of each.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat in skillet; pour off fat.
Brown onions in oil until tender.
Add macaroni to meat mixture.
Add salt and pepper; stir well.
Add tomatoes, catsup, mushrooms, bay leaf and water.
Simmer for 30 minutes over low heat, stirring frequently.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: margarita(alcoholic drink)
directions: Mix lemon juice, tequila and Triple Sec.
Add ice.
Shake and strain into glass.

title: acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Place squash cut side down in apple juice mixture in roasting pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Turn cut side up and spoon apple juice over tops.
Bake 10 minutes more or until tender.
Spoon apple juice into center of squash just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown chops; combine other ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: school cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, baking powder, and soda.
Blend in dry ingredients (and peanut butter).
Drop on ungreased
cookie
sheet.
(For
large cookies drop a small "handful" of dough.) Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: Pour milk over oats, brown sugar, salt and shortening in a large bowl.
Pour the yeast into the warm water.
When milk mixture is lukewarm, add dissolved yeast and egg.
Mix in flour. Turn onto lightly floured board.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes. Knead until smooth. Place in greased bowl; let rise until double. Shape into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli with cheese
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Blend all ingredients in large bowl. Fold in broccoli; pour in baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add shortening to water; bring to a boil.
Add flour all at once and stir vigorously until ball forms in center of pan.
Cool slightly.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Mixture should be very stiff.
Drop on cookie sheet (greased) from spoon.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen small puffs.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut together until the size of small peas.
Add 1/3 cup of flour mixture to water.
Make a paste.
Add to rest of flour mixture.
Stir with fork until dough is moist and almost leaves sides of bowl.
Roll into ball.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 1 cup Miracle Whip salad dressing and 1 cup sour cream.
Pour over salad.

title: quick chili
directions: Cook onion. Add ground beef and cook until no longer pink. Add chili seasoning and stir. Add tomatoes or tomato sauce and water. Bring to a boil, add hot chili beans and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain shrimp or cook and clean fresh shrimp.
Combine with other ingredients.

title: hot cheese and sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage; drain and crumble.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Serve with Doritos or tostadas.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except chicken) in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Then push chicken pieces into mixture. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: good easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef; drain, then add ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes with covered lid on low heat.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: 125 year old walnut pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients as they are listed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: christmas beans
directions: Fry bacon and crumble; set aside to drain.
Fry onion in bacon grease until transparent.
Brown the hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage and drain fat.
Add zucchini, green peppers, celery slices, chopped onion, tomato juice and all seasonings. Cook slowly for several hours.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine salmon, egg and flour.
Form into patties and fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.

title: smashing mystery dessert
directions: Whip cream; fold in brandy.
Break cake into small pieces. Fold into cream.
Spoon into clean 9 x 13-inch dish.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours to overnight.
Spoon into bowls and serve.

title: souper enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in hot oil in skillet 2 to 3 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons hot oil into skillet.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, chicken, water, cumin and green chilies.
Heat well.
Spoon about 1/3 cup into each tortilla.
Roll up and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour taco sauce over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then 45 minutes at 325°.
Makes 3 pies.

title: wild tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, salsa and tuna.
Mix until smooth as possible (may also add chopped green onion, jalapeno, black olives, etc.).
Spread mixture on tortilla (leave 1/2-pinch on edge).
Roll tightly and refrigerate until firm.
When ready to serve, slice in 1/2-inch slices.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or just until turning a little golden.
Remove from oven and cool completely.

title: ham-broccoli-cheese pie
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; chop coarsely.
In unbaked pie shell spread 1/2 ham, broccoli, cheese and onion.
Repeat layers. Gradually stir the milk into the beaten egg; add seasonings. Pour carefully on top of filled pie.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons cheese on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 325°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves six.

title: spaghetti omelette
directions: Mix all together.
Place in hot pan of olive oil; cover and brown on one side.
Sprinkle with more cheese and place under broiler until brown.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate covered seafoam
directions: Cook to 300°.
Remove and mix in 1 tablespoon of soda and pour into a well-oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
This will foam up a lot when you add the soda and you must be fast in putting it into pan.
The pan should be set on a cake rack so it will cool faster, and it will be not so likely to fall either.
When cool, break and dip into melted chocolate and you have Sea Foam Candy.
Better than you'd buy at the store.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Option:
Instead of using cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, allspice and ground cloves, use 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice mix.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then add milk.
Cook on medium heat until soft ball stage.
(This is when small amount dropped in cold water can be formed into small ball.)
Stir in margarine until well blended and cook a few minutes longer.
The fudge should be stirred constantly while cooking.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and salt.
Beat mixture until it becomes glossy.
Add pecans.
Mix well.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Season and brown chicken in a little shortening.
Place in a casserole.
Cook onion and celery in skillet until tender.
Add rice, soup and water; heat.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° about 55 minutes.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Wash all vegetables.
Cut lettuce to bite size pieces.
Chop next 4 ingredients to bite size and layer them one by one.
Spread frozen peas over salad.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Spread Mozzarella cheese over salad.
Stir sugar and mayonnaise together until completely mixed.
Spread over entire salad.
Boil eggs until hard-boiled and place in refrigerate until next day.

title: potpourri pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Mix the ingredients in a large bowl in the order given and mix until well blended, 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes until it tests done.
Do not overbake.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: With hand mixer, beat oleo, shortening and sugar together. Add flour; beat well.
Add milk and vanilla. Beat well until fluffy.
Add food coloring of your choice.

title: salmon-cheese loaf
directions: Drain salmon or tuna.
Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Put mixture into loaf pan and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all remaining ingredients; pour over butter.
Pour fruit over top (don't mix). Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until the dry ingredients are moist.
(Do not overmix.)
Pour into a greased loaf pan (9 x 5-inch) and bake approximately 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: uncooked quick pie
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and milk. Stir in lemonade or limeade. Pour mixture into graham cracker crust shell. Put into refrigerator until set. Decorate with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Melt butter with unsweetened chocolate.
Remove from heat. Add eggs and sugar to mixture.
Mix well the baking powder, salt, vanilla, flour and chocolate chips.
Mix all together well.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll dough into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Place on cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Add soup, ketchup, mustard, Tabasco, salt, pepper and enough water to reach desired consistency.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter.
Do not stir!
Heat in microwave on High 4 1/2 to 6 minutes or until butter is melted.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir until smooth. Spread in well-greased pan (13 x 9-inch).
(For Rocky Road Fudge, coarsely chop nuts and add 1 cup miniature marshmallows.)
Serves 15 to 20.

title: beefed-up biscuit casserole
directions: Stir ground beef, onion and green peppers
and cook until brown.
Let cool and add tomato sauce, garlic and chili powder. Mix cheese, sour cream and egg.
Beat well.
Add to meat mixture. Using canned biscuits, line a baking dish with 5 biscuits to make a crust.
Pour over this the meat mixture.
Then spread the other 5 biscuits on top of the meat mixture and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Grate cabbage.
Set aside Top Ramen soup and slivered almonds. Mix the rest of the ingredients for dressing; mix with cabbage. Just before serving, add soup mix and slivered almonds.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple (reserving juice) and place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix flour and sugar; sprinkle over pineapple. Sprinkle grated cheese over pineapple.
Spoon pineapple juice on cheese.
Crush Ritz crackers and place on top of casserole.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Good with ham or grilled meats.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and sugar; add half and half; mix well. Blend in eggs; add pineapple, coconut, bananas and cherries; stir well.
Add frozen strawberries and pecans; mix well.
Chill; churn-freeze.

title: dick boyett's blue mountain crappie fry
directions: Fish fillets are preferably crappie, but okay if other species. Put buttermilk in mid size bowl.
Add mustard until cream colored. Add salt and pepper.
Stir.
Put fillets in about 30 minutes prior to cooking.
Soak.
Use dutch oven or large cast iron skillet.
Get oil deep enough to float fish when done.
Heat oil to 365°.
This is critical.
If too hot, fish will brown too quick and not cook inside.
Drain fish, use a colander.
Have cornmeal prepared with salt and pepper mixed in to taste.
Roll fish in cornmeal.
When temperature is right, put fish in.
Do not put in too many, it drops the temperature too fast.
When fish starts to the surface, leave in about 2 minutes more, then take out.
Put on paper towels and keep warm.
Cook more fillets making sure temperature is 365°.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Blend together soup and flour.
Add sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in broccoli.
Turn into casserole dish.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Combine and beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Watch carefully so crust won't burn. Cool before cutting.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix 3 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ham rolls
directions: Melt
the butter.
Add mustard, poppy seed
and
onion. Slice rolls horizontally.
Remove top portion.
Spread top and bottom of rolls with butter mixture.
Combine ham
and
cheese and place on roll bottoms, then cover with roll tops.
Bake in roll
container for
10 to 15 minutes in 400° oven.
(May
be frozen and reheated!)

title: banana ice cream
directions: Blend ingredients together well and freeze in an ice cream churn until firm.

title: parmesan toast
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut baguette at a sharp angle into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Spread both sides with margarine and place on a baking sheet.
Toast in oven until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Rub garlic clove on one side of toast and top with Parmesan.
Return to oven and toast until cheese is golden brown.

title: easy homestyle macaroni and cheese
directions: *Substitute low-fat or nonfat sour cream for regular sour cream.

title: sesame cheese balls
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, cheddar cheese, celery, onion, garlic salt, seasoned salt and hot pepper sauce. Beat until well blended.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in sesame seeds.
Cover, refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.

title: twenty-four hour slaw
directions: Boil together the first 5 ingredients.
Cut up vegetables and combine.
Pour sauce over cabbage mixture and mix well.
Best if left in refrigerator overnight.

title: garlic-parsley potatoes
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss to coat well.
Layer half of potato mixture in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle half of parsley over potatoes. Layer remaining potato mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Uncover and sprinkle remaining parsley over potatoes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk and bring to a rapid boil.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add oats, nuts and vanilla. Stir well.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: german potato salad
directions: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add potatoes; cook until tender but still firm, about 15 minutes. Drain, cool, and chop. Place bacon in a large, deep skillet. Cook over medium high heat until evenly brown. Drain, crumble, and set aside. Reserve bacon fat. Add the flour, sugar, water, and vinegar to skillet and cook in reserved bacon fat over medium heat until dressing is thick. Add bacon, potatoes, and green onions to skillet and stir until coated. Cook until heated and season with salt and pepper. Serve warm.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake at 325° until done.

title: bacon stix
directions: Dredge one side of each bacon strip in cheese.
Roll the coated bacon diagonally around bread sticks, cheese side inward.
Place sticks on a paper towel-lined platter.
Microwave at High for 4 to 6 minutes until bacon begins to brown.
Rotate plate once.
Roll each stick in cheese again.

title: butter cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, salt, egg and vanilla in a mixing bowl until light, fluffy and smooth.
Add flour and mix well.
Form into ball and chill.
Roll out chilled dough to 1/8-inch thickness and cut with assorted cookie cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and decorate.

title: punch
directions: Add equal amounts of each juice; mix well and add as much orange sherbet as desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil fryer.
Cool and debone.
Melt oleo in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Drain off in cup and save.
Put boned chicken in buttered casserole dish.

title: crab soup
directions: Simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: italian cake with filling
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly; add sugar and beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold in alternately with lemon extract and water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, slice cake in half to make 2 layers.

title: dump salad
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Pour into container; let chill.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Fold pineapple and bananas in jello mixture.
Put marshmallows on top and let set until firm. Then ice with Sauce for Frosted Fruit Salad.

title: haystack candy
directions: Melt together the butterscotch chips, peanut butter and white chocolate.
Then add nuts and Chinese noodles.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let sit until firm.

title: mom's best frozen corn
directions: Mix together and simmer for 10 minutes.
Put the kettle in ice cubes.
Chill well.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: watergate salad(quick!  light!  delicious!  no cooking!)
directions: Open pudding mix into a large bowl.
Add drained canned fruit to dry pudding mix, stir thoroughly.
Add coconut, nuts, fresh fruits or other "optional" goodies.
Spoon in Cool Whip; mix well (refrigerate if necessary).
Eat!
Enjoy!
Yum!
Serves approximately 10 to 15.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Arrange layers of bananas, nuts and coconut in cooked pie shell.
Cook pineapple, flour and sugar over low heat until thick. Cool and spread over banana mixture.
Put Cool Whip on top. Makes 2 pies.

title: fluffy punch
directions: Mix lemonade, orange juice, ice cream, sherbet and water in large punch bowl.
Make ice ring, if desired.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Melt shortening.
Saute potatoes with parsley, onion, bay leaf, salt and pepper over medium heat, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix eggplant and eggs; beat well.
Combine other ingredients. Mix well.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° until done.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 8 wedges.
Arrange potatoes with skin sides down in 2 shallow baking pans.
Mix ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender, brushing occasionally with oil mixture.

title: vanilla butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a slow rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Cook to 235°, remove and cool without stirring.

title: snowy mt. mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes as you would for mashed potatoes.
Drain.
Put in mixing bowl with following:
cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Beat at high speed.
Beat in enough milk to make mashed potato consistency.
Fold in chives.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Mix milk, vanilla, egg, sugar, flour and salt.
Add sliced apples.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks.
Add the salt with the whites, too.
When soft peaks form, add sugar, Karo syrup and vanilla.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread on cake.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add eggs, beating after each.
Add baking powder, baking soda and buttermilk.
Add all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: california guacamole
directions: Scoop the avocado from the shells, leaving about a 1/8 inch rim.
Squeeze the lemon juice over the empty shell halves and pulp.
Mash the pulp and combine with remaining ingredients to make the filling.
Return the filling to the shells.
Serve with chips.

title: 1926 white fruit cake 1976(from hettie prevatt)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add others in order given.
Pour into cans and steam 3 hours.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: apricot muffins
directions: In a bowl, pour the boiling water over the dried apricot pieces.
Set aside to cool.
In a large bowl, sift together the flours, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir the eggs, oil and orange juice into the liquid apricot mixture.

Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and add the liquid apricot mixture, stirring enough to moisten (do not overmix). Spray two 12-muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray or line with muffin cups.
Fill each 2/3 full with batter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: crispix mix
directions: Put oleo, syrup, brown sugar and salt in large microwave bowl. Cook on High 2 minutes in microwave. Stir. Repeat for 2 minutes. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon baking soda. Stir. Pour over Crispix in brown paper bag and mix with spoon. Microwave in bag on High 1 1/2 minutes; shake. Repeat for 1 1/2 minutes. Shake 1 minute. Add pretzels and peanuts. Shake. Cool. Add M&M's.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Place into a blender with chocolate chips and blend for 20 seconds.
Add egg yolks and blend for another 30 seconds.
Fold in whipping cream and powdered sugar; blend well.
Chill for about 2 hours.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In large pot, fill with water and add stew meat.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for about 30 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until the vegetables are tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients except crackers.
Crush the crackers and sprinkle over mixture in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix all together; stuff mushrooms.
Dot top of mushrooms with butter. Bake stuffed down on cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes. Can be left in oven on warm.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots in round slices.
Cook until tender with salt. Drain carrots.
Add all ingredients while carrots are still warm. Let set 1 or more days in refrigerator.

title: tasty pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Spread mustard on both sides and flour.
Brown chops in hot grease.
Drain off grease and lower temperature to simmer.
Add 2 cans of chicken and rice soup and 1 can of water.
Cook for 45 minutes on low heat.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips and chill.
Serve with chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and pour over first ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Stir and serve.

title: easy clam puff
directions: Stir margarine into warm milk to melt.
Stir in clams, eggs, onion, salt and pepper to blend.
Stir in crackers until thoroughly blended.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake in preheated 350° oven until puffed and golden, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with sauce made of soup blended with 1/2 cup milk or water.
Serves 4.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Combine ingredients and serve with chips or vegetables.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together and put in a bowl.
Put the next 4 ingredients (oleo, shortening, cocoa and water) in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Put the flour and sugar in next.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Put in a greased pan and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon ice cream pie
directions: Soften lemonade and ice cream.
Beat together until creamy. Pour into graham cracker crusts and freeze until serving time. Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs and lemon rind.

title: egg-asparagus-mushroom casserolea wonderful friday luncheon dish!
directions: Melt butter, add flour and blend well. Combine mustard with soup and add to flour mixture. Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thick. In a buttered casserole arrange a layer of half the drained asparagus, then half the eggs and half the sauce.Repeat. Refrigerate or set aside. When ready, combine rice cereal and cheese and sprinkle over the top. Place in a 350° oven, uncovered and bake until hot through, about 35 minutes. Serves 4

title: two salads in one
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Mix gently, cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve marinated vegetables in lettuce cups.

title: pizza bread
directions: Thaw and let frozen bread dough rise as instructed on package. Roll into 2 large circles.
Fry sausage and drain.
Place 1/2 of sausage on each dough circle.
Spread 1/2 of Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese on top of sausage.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of each seasoning.
Roll up, jelly roll style; seal all edges and place, seam side down, on cookie sheet. Brush top with melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle top with additional parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until top is golden brown.

title: new england baked beans
directions: Rinse beans; add to 2 quarts cold water.
Boil and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover.
Let stand 1 hour or add beans to water and soak overnight.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to beans and cooking water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until beans are tender, about 1 hour.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Combine sugar, molasses, mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in 2 cups reserved liquid.
Add mixture to beans, salt pork and onion in 2-quart bean pot or casserole.
Stir to blend.
Cover; bake at 300° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add more bean liquid or water if needed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Continue beating and add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture. Fold in nuts if desired.
Spoon into three greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cool bread on rack.
Delicious with butter or cheese spread.
Freezes very well.

title: paula's recital punch
directions: Combine juices and sugar; chill.
Just before serving, add ice cubes, ginger ale and club soda.

title: baked rice
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grape pie
directions: Combine all, except butter.
Place in pie shell; dot with butter.
Place top crust, leaving vent slits.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: spring fruit salad(serves 6)
directions: In a bowl, combine first five ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate over night.
Just before serving, sprinkle with walnuts and brown sugar.
Garnish with mint if desired.

title: bean pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Heat beans in 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling. Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Cover and cook until tender, 5 to 10 minutes; drain.
Mix beans, mushrooms, onion, garlic and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edges comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: company ribs
directions: Brown ribs.
Pour off excess grease.
Pour sauce over ribs. Cover; simmer for about 45 minutes, or until tender.

title: cottage mashed potatoes
directions: Decreasing the water by 1/2 cup, prepare the potatoes according to package directions, but add the onion to the boiling water before adding the potatoes.
With a fork, fold in the cottage cheese.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: buttered egg noodles with poppy seed
directions: Boil a large quantity of water on top of stove to cook noodles. Salt water. Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain noodles in colander, reserving half of the boiling water and returning it to the cooking pot.

Cover to keep warm. Place butter in 1-cup glass measuring cup; melt on High. Toss with noodles in bowl. Transfer buttered noodles back to colander; set over hot water and cover until serving time. Before serving, return noodles to bowl and toss with poppy seed.

title: au gratin potatoes and peas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Reduce heat.
Add milk and stir.
Cook until thickens (white sauce).
Add cheese to sauce.
Stir until cheese melts.
Combine potatoes, peas and chopped pimento in a casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Mix together well except chili powder. Form into ball and roll in chili powder. Wrap tightly. Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: cheerios treats
directions: Place the butter and marshmallows in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Micro uncovered on High for 2 minutes or until puffed.
Stir in peanut butter until blended.
Add cereal and M&M's; mix well. Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Press down gently.
Cool slightly before cutting.
Yields 15 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots; combine in bowl.
Add mayonnaise and vinegar in 3 to 1 ratio to taste.
After combining all ingredients, "cream" with a small amount of milk.
Remember that taste of slaw will get "sharper" over time.

title: tomato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce cups.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Drain and fill lettuce cups with tomato mixture.
Thirty-five calories.

title: fresh blueberry pie(delicious and different)
directions: Combine 1/2 c. water, sugar and 1 c. blueberries; bring to a boil; remove from heat. Make a paste of 1/4 c. water, flour, and salt; stir into hot blueberry mixture until thickened. Stir in remaining 3 cups blueberries and let cool. Pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate. When cold, top with Cool Whip.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice off cherries and pineapple.
Bring to a boil, pour over Jell-O to dissolve and chill.
Add Coke combined with cherries and pineapple.
Cream nuts and cheese together.
Fold into mixture and chill.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cook until thick.
Add 1 cup pecans, chopped.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°.

title: sensational salsa
directions: In medium size bowl combine all ingredients and mix well. Cover and let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Salsa will get hotter the longer it stands.

title: easy low-fat chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and seasonings and remaining water (3 1/2 cups).
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Yields 7 servings.

title: tuna or chicken jackstraw casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, reserving 1 cup of shoestring potatoes to sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: honey glazed barbecued chicken
directions: Wash and season chicken.
Place chicken in either an aluminum pan or in a pan lined with aluminum foil.
Preheat oven at 450°. Place chicken in oven.
Mix in a large bowl the honey and the barbecue sauce.
As the chicken browns, brush on the mixture of honey and barbecue sauce on both sides of the chicken.
Complete cooking until chicken is tender, approximately 45 minutes.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine fruit. In small bowl, combine yogurt, lemon
juice, sugar and vanilla. Mix well together.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: low-fat mayonnaise
directions: Place all ingredients, except oil, in blender and mix at high speed.
Slowly add the oil, blending constantly.
If too thick, thin with a few drops of lemon juice.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients. Heat until boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour. Serve over chips.

title: 7-minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler. Beat with rotary beater or electric mixer for 1 minute. Place over boiling water and beat until frosting stands in glossy peaks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken for 1 hour, cool and remove from bone.
Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on box.
Mix soups, onion, celery and one-half of the stuffing together in a bowl.
Place mixture in bottom of a casserole dish.
Add chicken pieces.
Add sliced Velveeta cheese over chicken.
Put remaining stuffing on top of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together at medium speed. Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with the milk to the first mixture.
Add vanilla and beat 1 minute.
Pour into muffin pans and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, cream butter, Crisco, eggs and sugar together.
Add flour, milk and flavorings.
Mix on high for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour, until top is golden brown.
Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: microwave pralines
directions: In a large (at least 10 cups) microwave safe bowl, mix brown sugar and cream until there are no big lumps.
Put in the microwave, uncovered, on high for 11-14 minutes.
Carefully remove the hot bowl and stir in softened butter, cut into 8-10 pats.
Add pecans.
Let sit for a minute to thicken, then drop by tablespoonfuls onto foil or waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl combine meat, onions, soup mix, green pepper, egg, catsup, bread crumbs and water.
Shape into loaf and place in baking pan or bowl.
Bake about 1 hour or until done.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter. Slowly bring to a boil and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter. Blend well. Add oats and nuts. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Beat soda into other 1/2 cup buttermilk until it doubles in size.
Add to mixture.
Add Crisco and beat.
Add flour and baking powder.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Roll out 1/4 and cut with cookie cutters.
Sugar tops.
Bake for 5 minutes at 450°.

title: barbecued dolphin
directions: Rinse dolphin and pat dry.
Put dolphin in nonreactive pan. Heat up butter in pan.
Add hot sauce and lemon juice.
Let butter mixture cool a little. Pour over dolphin.
Let sit for 10 minutes. Put dolphin on grill and baste with remaining butter mixture. Dolphin is ready when it flakes easily.

title: blueberry-banana pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar until smooth. Line bottom of crust with bananas after dipping in the lemon juice.
Pour half the cream cheese mixture in each crust lined with bananas.
Top with pie filling and chill for 4 hours before serving.

title: crunchy garden salad
directions: Thaw peas; drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.
Mix dressing and mustard and pour over salad.
Toss and chill.
Makes a lot.
Great for entertaining.

title: easy cherry cobbler(microwave)
directions: Mix pie filling and almond extract together.
Put in a 10-inch pie plate.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes. Stir after 2 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine vegetables; stir in dressing. Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: golden glazed carrots
directions: Scrape carrots; cut in 1-inch chunks and cook in small amount of water until barely tender.
Drain, if necessary.
Add butter or margarine, brown sugar and some grated lemon rind or lemon juice. Heat slowly, stirring occasionally until nicely glazed.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mash together and
fry	in 3 to 4 tablespoons olive oil in 1/2-inch patties.
Makes 4 to 6 good size patties.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let bread dough rise.
Fry sausage completely and drain off fat.
Set aside.
Saute mushrooms, green pepper and onion until tender.
Turn burner off; stir in cheese.
Add sausage; stir until cheese is melted.
Roll out dough.
Put half of sausage mixture in middle.
Fold one side, then other.
Brush dough with egg whites. Repeat with other dough.
Bake in bread pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can also be made with cold meats and other cheeses. Let cool, then slice.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip salted chicken into buttermilk; roll dipped chicken in Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with sweet potatoes.
Drain syrup from potatoes.
Save about 1/2 cup syrup and dump in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of brown sugar over potatoes and cut 1/2 of butter up in slices.
Drop over potatoes.
Mix flour and milk together and dump over potatoes.
Melt remainder of butter and mix with 1/2 cup of brown sugar.
Dump over top.
Sprinkle on pecans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven, sprinkle marshmallows over top and put back in oven until marshmallows are brown.

title: frog roll
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix together with seasoning.
Form 3 logs.
Roll in chopped walnuts or pecans.

title: sausage pie
directions: Mix and roll as for pie crust to fit 2 (9-inch) pie tins. Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Dice ham, green onions and cheese.
Add bacon bits, salt and pepper.
Knead into cream cheese.
Mold into ball.
May garnish with paprika.
Wrap with Reynolds Wrap and store in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: dilly beans
directions: Snip off ends of beans; drop a third of the beans at a time in boiling water for five minutes or until tender and crisp.
Lift beans out with slotted spoon; pack upright in sterilized pint jars.
Place two tablespoons dill and a half clove of garlic in each jar.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat and set aside. Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, salt and cornstarch and beat until smooth.
Mix in the melted chocolate, then add Carnation milk.
Pour into crust.
Mix nuts and coconut.
Sprinkle on top of filling.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; rinse and set aside in large serving bowl.
Dice tomatoes and chop ham.
Add Italian dressing to pasta and stir well.
Add tomatoes, ham and black olives.
Stir well.
Chill and serve with favorite meat.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Combine boiling water and molasses and stir in baking soda (mixture will foam).
Arrange alternate layers of crumb and molasses mixture in pie shell, beginning and ending with crumb mixture.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until top and crust are browned and filling set.
Cool.
Serve plain or topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: fruit cake cookies(a very good friend shared this recipe with me)
directions: *Mix with 1 cup flour that has been reserved.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: In big bowl, stir together first 4 ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles crumbs.
Combine eggs, mashed potatoes and milk.
Add at once into dry ingredients.
Knead gently on floured board, 10 or 12 strokes.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick. Cut out with biscuit butter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in a 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grandpa's salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and save half of the juice.
Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Set aside.
Mix together the celery, onion and crumbled dried bread.
Add eggs and butter.
Mix.
Add salmon and small amount of juice.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 5-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato "pie"
directions: Place half of the toast in bottom of well-greased pan. Place half of the tomatoes over the toast. Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar on the tomatoes to taste. Combine the mayonnaise, milk and cream cheese. Mix well. Spread half of this mixture over the tomatoes. Top with half of the grated cheese. Then repeat the layers with the remainder of the ingredients. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: see's fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter together.
Add vanilla, eggs, powdered sugar and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered foil-lined 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate and cut into pieces.
Keep refrigerated.

title: country gravy
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in flour until blended.
Add milk and chicken broth, stirring, cooking until thick.
Add paprika, which gives a good color, 1 teaspoon pepper and salt to taste.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown ground beef and drain, then add barbecue sauce, instant minced onion and brown sugar.
Now take the biscuits.
Press each into an ungreased muffin cup, making sure dough goes up to edge of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk and bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir and blend in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Then mix the remaining (except nuts).
Combine the two mixtures together and add nuts.
Pour into bread pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken mixture and set back in refrigerator to chill. Mix all ingredients together, then add to chicken mixture. Refrigerate and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cook all together until pickles are clear. Pack in hot jars and seal. Follow manufacturer's recommendation on lids and rings. Use canning jars only.

title: perfect pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, 1/3 cup water and pumpkin.
Sift together the next 6 ingredients.
Gradually beat into first mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured large loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans or 20 cupcake pans.
Bake all sizes in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: string pie
directions: Brown hamburg with onions and peppers in a large skillet; drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, Parmesan cheese, eggs and butter; mix well.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cottage cheese; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in top of double boiler.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks, milk and water.
Cook over simmering water until thick.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Save 1/4 coconut for meringue.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell; top with meringue and sprinkle with coconut.
Bake until light brown in 350° oven.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread mixture on the tortilla.
Roll. Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill, then slice into bite-size pieces. Serve with taco sauce.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Stir ingredients together and put into crust.
Chill and serve.

title: the reverend's meat loaf
directions: Mix together but not overmixing, it will be tough if you do. Put in aluminum foil-lined loaf pan.
Cover with sides of boil. Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Serve with ketchup or steak sauce. Serves about 8.
Season to taste.

title: church men's breakfast casserole
directions: Night Before:
Brown sausage; drain. Beat lightly the eggs, milk and dry mustard. In 9 x 13-inch pan, put sausage, croutons and cheese. Pour egg mixture over; refrigerate overnight.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Mix and allow to set 2 or 3 days; will keep 3 weeks.

title: banana split
directions: Mix 1 stick softened margarine with graham cracker crumbs. Pat out in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix confectioners sugar, eggs and remaining margarine (margarine should be soft). Beat until thick.
If needed, add another cup of sugar.
Spread over top of crumb mixture.
Split bananas lengthwise and lay on top of other mixture.
Spread the drained pineapple over the bananas.
Spread the Cool Whip over the pineapple.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and arrange cherries on top.
Chill for several hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Mix.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mix.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 325° for 45 minutes or so.
Can make two smaller loaves.
Freezes well.

title: apple-raisin betty
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease an 8-inch square baking pan. Place apples and raisins in pan.
Combine lemon juice and water. Sprinkle over fruit.
Mix together flour, sugar and spices; blend thoroughly.
Stir in corn flakes.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake about 35 minutes or until apples are tender and top is lightly browned.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt ingredients all together in a pan.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Place pan into a large bowl of ice cold water.
Ice cubes may be needed to keep water good and cold. Beat until thick enough to spread.
Do not use flavorings.
This will cover a large tube cake.
Double ingredients and cook 1 minute longer for larger cake.

title: italian delight casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix softened cream cheese, sour cream and onions. Set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce, garlic, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, put alternate layers of spaghetti, beef mixture and cream cheese mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: roast beef and noodles
directions: Cook the roast beef.
When done, add tomatoes and celery seed to broth.
When the mixture comes to a boil, add some cooked noodles.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Cut each cheese slice in half; place half on top of each cutlet. Starting with a short end, tightly roll up cutlets.
Tie securely with string. On waxed paper, combine flour and pepper; mix well. Add cutlets; toss gently to coat.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Stir mix with 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup water and 2 egg yolks in a medium saucepan.
Stir in 2 cups water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Pour into cooled, baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
In Pyrex dish add melted butter and cream in sugar.
Add
milk
and
flour.
Drain
peaches and place on mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Gather	sassafras leaves in month of August (preferably in full
moon).
Pick	leaves	off
branches
and put in clean sacks (pillow case
or
sacks
made of old sheets.) Don't fill sacks full or tight; about half so you can have plenty of room and shake up	every
day.
Each
morning, put outdoors to dry, not in the sun,
under
carport.
Let dry until they are very brittle.

title: face paint
directions: Mix well.
Put cold cream on face.
Then apply paint.

title: mushrooms in cream sauce(servings: 4)
directions: Clean mushrooms and slice in half if large.
Pat dry.
Fry bacon in a large pan until lightly browned.
Remove from pan and reserve.
Add the butter to the pan drippings.
Add onions; saute until lightly browned.
Add mushrooms; cook until tender, stirring often.
Stir in wine, salt, pepper, paprika, nutmeg and mace. Cover frypan and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Off the heat, add the cooked bacon, cream and lemon juice.
Reheat until just warm.
Do not let the mixture boil!!!
Garnish with parsley and serve with noodles or dumplings.

title: poppin' popovers
directions: Note: The secret is to start with a cold oven.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to soften.
Carefully stir in pineapple, pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Chill well.
Roll into ball while adding chopped pecans.

title: nitey-nites
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat 5 minutes.
Blend in cooled chocolate.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with ice water, beating well after each addition.
Bake in 2 well-greased and floured 8-inch round pans in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
(This can also be baked in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.)

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt in a bowl and mix well with fork. Add Crisco and mix with fork until crumbly.
In small bowl, mix water, vinegar and egg.
Combine the two mixtures and mix well. Divide dough into five portions and shape into flat and round. Wrap in waxed paper and chill at least 1/2 hour.
Also, may be frozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, put a layer of beans, drained, and a layer of French fried onions, saving some of larger ones for top decorating.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and slice.
Layer potatoes, cucumbers and onions.
Mix other ingredients well and pour over vegetables. Cover and chill.

title: peach glaze
directions: Mix preserves and water in saucepan. Cook and stir over low heat until thick and smooth. Spread glaze over top of loaf. Garnish loaf with peach slices, red maraschino cherries and parsley, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to soften.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes.
Shape into a ball, roll in chopped nuts.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onions very fine.
Put into a large bowl.
Add 1/3 cup sugar and mix well.
Using the back of a large spoon, press cabbage down for 15 minutes.
In a small pan, combine 1 teaspoon sugar, mustard, celery seed, salt and white vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add Wesson oil.
Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: 5 layer supreme
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, melt 5 tablespoons butter and mix with cinnamon crisp.
Place on bottom of pan.
Next, mix powdered sugar, 1 stick butter and 2 eggs.
Place over first layer.
Add sliced bananas and place on second layer.
Add 1 can undrained crushed pineapple.
Place a layer of Cool Whip on top.
Walnuts and maraschino cherries may be added for decoration.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Combine sugar, egg, 2 tablespoons flour, salt and 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir in rhubarb and spread mixture in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine 4 tablespoons butter, 2/3 cup flour and brown sugar.
Cut into crumbs and spread over rhubarb mixture. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with cold milk.

title: one dish meal casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook potatoes and whip until smooth.
Add corn, beans and onion into simmering beef.
Remove from stove and pour into casserole dish.
Top with whipped potatoes; sprinkle cheese over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sausage chowder
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put in a large pot.
Add all ingredients except bell pepper and potatoes.
Cook 1 hour on medium to low heat.
Add peppers and potatoes; cook 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Better if it sets overnight.

title: creamed herring salad
directions: Drain herring of wine sauce and dice into bite-sized pieces. Put in mixing bowl.
Grate carrot into same bowl.
Dice cucumber, pepper and radishes into bowl.
Add diced scallions.
Add desired amount of sour cream to moisten and sugar to taste.
Mix.

title: grandma rosie's baked macaroni
directions: In casserole dish, spread layer of tomato sauce in bottom (1/2 the sauce).
Add macaroni, rest of sauce and half the grated cheese.
Mix well and spread evenly in pan.
Top with the remainder of cheese and put pats of butter or margarine on top (6 to 8 pats).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until top is crusty and browned.
(A pound of cooked and drained ground beef can also be added.)

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Roll out 1 package of crescent rolls in bottom of 11 x 9-inch pan with bottom greased.
Put in a layer of ham, Swiss cheese, broccoli, then ham.
Mix soup, sour cream and mustard.
Pour over ham; top with layer of Swiss cheese and another package of crescent rolls.
Brush top with egg yolk mixed with 1 tablespoon water. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagne with cheese sauce
directions: In a large skillet heat oil over medium heat.
Add onions, red peppers, mushrooms and garlic.
Cook, stirring, 8 minutes or until tender.
In large bowl combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, 1/2 cup Parmesan and salt.
Stir in spinach and vegetables.

title: spiced peaches
directions: To the peach juice, add sugar, vinegar, cloves and cinnamon. Bring to a boil and cook 20 minutes.
Pour over peaches.
Keep in refrigerator for at least 24 hours before serving.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together; pour into buttered casserole.
Bake until bubbly and top with herbed bread crumbs and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with mixed fresh fruit, if desired.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Add milk to peanut butter; blend well and add to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake in greased loaf pan in slow oven 45 to 50 minutes.
It is best when a day old.

title: fruit-ginger ale punch
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: baked cranberry relish
directions: In an ovenproof pan with lid, bake for 1 hour at 350° the cranberries, sugar and cinnamon.
Stir once or twice.
Remove from oven and add the rest of the ingredients.

title: chicken waldorf sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients; spread on bread of your choice and top with second slice of bread.
Serves 6.

title: corn stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove a 1/4-inch slice from the stem end of the tomato and scoop out the seeds with a spoon.
Turn the tomato shell upside down and drain on paper towels.
Work from top to bottom of the ears of corn; use a sharp knife to cut off the kernels.
Place the kernels in a medium mixing bowl with green onions, bell pepper, black pepper and mayonnaise.
Combine the ingredients to form a thick mixture.

title: sausage squash special
directions: Brown sausage and garlic in frying pan; drain.
Cook squash just until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain.
Stir squash and next 6 ingredients into sausage.
Fold in eggs.
Place in casserole dish and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: walnut torta
directions: Beat egg yolks plus 2 whole eggs well.
Add whiskey and sugar. Beat well for 3 minutes with an electric mixer.
Remove from mixer and fold in walnuts.
Fold in flour and toast.
Add vanilla. Beat egg whites with a dash of salt and cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Now fold egg yolk mixture into whites.
Mix.
Pour into pan and bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: new england cole slaw
directions: Put cabbage and vegetables in bowl.
Combine and mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve with seafood, poultry, etc.

title: chocolate mochi
directions: Mix ingredients together,
then pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: stir-fried pork with cashews
directions: Heat oil in wok or heavy skillet over high heat.
Add pork and stir-fry until lightly browned, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce and stir-fry 1 minute.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in carrot julienne.
Cover and cook until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Add bell peppers and cashews and stir-fry until bell peppers are crisp-tender, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved, about 1 minute.
Push pork and vegetables to side.
Dissolve cornstarch in water in small bowl and add to wok.
Stir until sauce thickens and clears, about 1 minute.
Mix pork and vegetables into sauce.
Season with salt.
Serve immediately.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together ingredients; keep in a sealed container.

title: vegetable relish salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and pimento.
Mix all vegetables in a large bowl with tight lid.
Bring sugar, vinegar, oil, water and spices to a boil in saucepan; boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover with a tight lid.
Refrigerate overnight. Drain before serving.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes or to 234°.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour in greased (with butter) 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: broccoli-rice and shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma kilpatrick's goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
In separate pan, cook macaroni. Mix macaroni with beef mixture, then add 2 cups water and let simmer.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken strips; cook until done.
Strip 2 bell peppers (red and green) and onion.
Cook in 2 tablespoons of oil until tender and soft.
Add minced garlic. Then add cooked chicken and vegetables into same pan.
Cook 2 minutes until warm.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.
Squeeze 1 lemon over dish.

title: crab mold
directions: Melt cream cheese and cream of mushroom soup slowly.
Add gelatine.
Let cool.
When cool, add other ingredients.
Mix well. Mold overnight.

title: ashley's mexican bean dip
directions: Combine taco seasoning mix with sour cream.
Mix well.
Stir in softened cream cheese and can of bean dip.
Stir until smooth.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together until fluffy. Add 3/4 cup peanut butter.
Fold in one 8 ounce container Cool Whip.
Put in a graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: harvest cake
directions: Beat eggs, adding oil.
Add this to sugar and apples mixture. Sift flour and baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat 2 minutes. Add walnuts.
Fill 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of oleo with graham cracker crumbs; press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: delicious chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Spread in bottom of casserole dish, saving 1 cup of mixture.
Mix eggs, onion and celery to stuffing mixture.
Put chicken on top of mixture.
Pour soup over chicken.
Pour broth over soup.
Sprinkle cup of mixture over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown, about 30 or 40 minutes.

title: baked stuffed cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in flour. Gradually stir in milk. Stir until sauce is thick and smooth. Add salt, pepper, eggs and scallions.
Place the cauliflower in a greased baking dish. Cover the cauliflower with sauce, then bread crumbs and bake for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni 'n cheese in a crock-pot
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Add all ingredients in the crock-pot. Cook on low for 3 hours.

title: golden ham casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Spread one side of each piece with softened butter.
Combine meat and mustard.
Mix well.
Spread ham over half of bread slices.
Cover ham with remaining slices (sandwich style).
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir into milk with Worcestershire sauce.
Pour mixture over bread in 8-inch baking dish and let stand in refrigerator overnight; then place baking dish in pan with 1 inch of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until custard is set and knife comes out clean.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a medium bowl, combine soup and milk and then add beans and pepper.
Gently stir until the beans are coated with the soup/milk mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with onions and bake, uncovered, for an additional 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour; mix and then add vanilla, syrup and last pecans.
Stir until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: swedish tea logs
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, sugar and salt into bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until fine.
Add milk, egg and softened yeast.
Mix well.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Crush strawberries; put sugar in.
Make thick with Clear Jell. Take marshmallows and milk and melt over low heat.
Take off heat and let cool until it begins to jell, then add whipped cream. Also whip cream and marshmallows together.

title: california dip
directions: Mix together well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or longer.

title: yeast donuts
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and salt.
Crumble yeast into mixture. Add eggs and shortening (liquid).
Mix in flour.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Roll and cut out doughnuts.
Let stand 2 minutes before frying.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers extra fine.
Put into bottom of glass cake pan.
Combine sugar, vanilla, eggs and margarine.
Mix at high speed until creamy.
Spread evenly over wafers.
Arrange sliced bananas over sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with well drained pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over this; top with cherries and nuts.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in bowl with 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water.
Hollow out peppers, carefully removing seeds. Fill with meat mixture.
Place peppers in covered casserole. Pour remaining can tomato sauce over top of peppers.
Add 1 tomato sauce can of water and a bouillon cube in bottom of casserole. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Can use this same recipe for zucchini squash also.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Bake 350° for 45 minutes.
Mix all ingredients into bowl. Let stand 5 minutes.
For the perfect pie crust, buy Pillsbury pie crust and follow directions on the box.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Wash shrimp and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in butter. Add tomato paste and cream. Stir constantly so cream doesn't curdle. Add remaining ingredients except shrimp.
When mixture is hot, add shrimp and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve hot in pastry shells.

title: zucchini-cranberry holiday bread
directions: Preliminaries:
Generously grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans; set aside.

title: noodle or pasta salad
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water.
Drain.
Mix hot pasta with remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Season to taste.
Serve hot or cold.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread bean dip on big plate. Spread sour cream mixture on top of bean dip, then tomatoes and onions (green tops and all).
Top with olives and sprinkle with cheese.

title: frozen fruit
directions: Slice bananas and pour thawed juice over bananas.
Pour in fruit cocktail and juice.
Stir in frozen strawberries and mix. Pour all into bowl for freezing.
Before serving, let thaw about 10 to 15 minutes and serve while still icy.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough in a pizza or rectangle pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Boil water, sugar, cornstarch and jello to make a glaze.
Cool.
(May need to refrigerate to thicken.)
Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar and ice cookie dough.
Slice bananas and cover cheese layer.
Cover banana layer with cool, thickened glaze.
Top with any fruit assortment you desire.
Refrigerate.
I used Fruit Fresh to keep fruit from getting dark.

title: nut bread
directions: Let stand 15 minutes. Bake in greased pans 1 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: kringla(this is a norwegian cookie.)
directions: Whip the whipping cream.
Add (fold) in sour cream.
Let stand.
Beat together the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add whipping cream and sour cream mixture.
Slowly add remaining ingredients.
The dough will be very soft!
Chill dough overnight before forming cookies.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Combine
first	6
ingredients	in
a
large
bowl; add buttermilk,
egg and bacon drippings.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist.	Spoon batter into a preheated greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf
pan.	Bake
at 450° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Note:
Cornbread may be baked at 450° for 20 minutes in a preheated greased 10-inch iron skillet.

title: butterscotch ice cream sauce
directions: Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full, round boil (about 5 minutes). Let cool and add the evaporated milk. Stir well.

title: marbled chocolate bars
directions: Prepare cake mix as instructed on pkg.; pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1 baking pan.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar; stir in 1/4 c. chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls over batter; cut through batter with knife to swirl the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a tooth pick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.
Cut into bars. Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheese stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut a thin slice off the top of each pepper; remove seeds.
Parboil peppers in boiling water to cover for 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water; set aside.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients.	Mix
in
egg yolks, then milk a little at a time.	Cook until thick, stirring constantly.	Add butter and
flavoring.
Beat
egg	whites	for top and put in cooked, pastry shell.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in 4 layers at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes until center springs back when touched lightly.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Cook chicken
in
boiling
water
until
tender.
Drain chicken reserving 1 cup of the broth.
Cool chicken and remove chicken from bones;
cut in small pieces.
Combine soup, green chilies, chili powder,
onion,
garlic
powder,
hot sauce and reserved chicken broth and
blend well.
Cover bottom of 2 1/2 or 3 quart casserole
with
cups of the corn chips.
Spread half the chicken
over
corn
chips.
Add
half
of
the
soup mixture; add half
of the cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles in boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt added. Cook, uncovered, rapidly for 4 to 6 minutes.
Drain; rinse with hot water.
Mix noodles with tuna, mushroom soup, milk and grated cheese.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Garnish with crumbs. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: candied fruits
directions: Use canned, preserved or freshly cooked fruit.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine sugar and water.
Boil to soft ball stage. Add fruit and simmer until clear.
Allow to stand in syrup overnight.
Drain thoroughly.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place on cake rack. Dry in very slow oven until surface is firm.
Peaches, apples, prunes, figs, quinces, citron, plums, cherries and apricots may be used.
Dried fruits as well as fresh fruits may be prepared and candied.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef. Add onion and spaghetti sauce. Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: beef tips
directions: Using a black cast-iron skillet, heat oil and sear beef tips or meat of your choice, until browned. Add bell pepper, mushrooms and onions, saute until crisp tender. Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, then add vinegar and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil to dissolve bouillon cubes. Cook on medium-high heat for 10 to 15 minutes. Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 hours on low heat, stirring occasionally. (Do not rush simmer time.) Before serving, thicken with cornstarch or flour to your desired consistency.

title: speedy chicken stew
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring often.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes and lima beans are tender.
Stir in chicken, diced tomatoes and tomato paste; simmer 10 more minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, milk, and vanilla extract.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until slightly firm.
No crust necessary.

title: cocoa hidden (kisses) cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Combine flour and cocoa; blend in cream mixture.
Add nuts.
Beat on low speed until well blended.
Chill dough 1 hour or until very firm to handle.
Heat oven to 375°.
Mold scant tablespoon of dough around each Kiss, covering Kiss completely.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until almost set.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: meme's tuna salad
directions: Get the juice off tuna.
Put a little bitty bit mustard, mayonnaise and pickles.
Stir it up!
Stir it up!

title: one step pound cake
directions: Blend at low speed.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Cake is done when top of cake springs back when touched.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken breast hawaiian
directions: Bone chicken breasts and cut in half; dip in egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Season with salt.
Pan-fry in 1/4-inch hot fat in electric skillet at 360° until brown.
Remove fat from pan. Combine juices, cornstarch, curry and sugar.
Pour over chicken. Cover.
Cook slowly (210°) 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve on toast.
Top with slivered almonds.
Serves 4.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Add flour and chopped nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on unbuttered cookie sheet. Place in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Measure sugar and set aside.
Measure pumpkin into large saucepan.
Add spice and Sure-Jell and mix well.
Place over heat and stir until mixture comes to a hard boil.
Immediately add sugar and stir.
Bring to a full rolling boil and boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Ladle quickly into jars.
Seal or cover with paraffin wax.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread beans on platter or tray.
Cover with sour cream. Sprinkle with taco seasoning.
Cover with green onions, olives and cheese.
Spoon taco sauce over all.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a dutch oven, brown chicken in margarine.
Remove chicken. Add celery, onion and bell pepper; saute until tender.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients.	Bring to a boil, then simmer approximately 20 minutes.
Serves four.

title: joy's rum slush
directions: Mix and dissolve 1 cup of sugar in 1/2 cup of the water.
Mix in microwave to dissolve for 3 minutes.
Mix everything else together and put in freezer.
Stir every 3 hours until frozen. Good.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef, onions and salt until light brown.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese to Ragu mixture.
Cook lasagna noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Layer in greased large shallow baking dish as follows: noodles, sauce, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Provolone cheese.
Layer again, ending with all cheeses and Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, until bubbly all over.
Let cool 10 minutes to firm up before cutting.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except raw shrimp.
Blend well.
Add shrimp to marinade and let set several hours in the refrigerator. To grill, place shrimp on a screen or grate with small holes. Grill 8 to 10 minutes over medium fire, basting often.
These can also be broiled.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: marinated oyster crackers
directions: Mix Wesson oil and dressing mix together.
Add garlic powder, dill weed and lemon pepper to mixture.
Pour the mixture over unsalted oyster crackers in a large container with a seal-tight lid.
Stir.
Shake the mixture every 30 minutes for 2 to 3 hours.

title: bud's banana surprise
directions: Slice a banana lengthwise.
Fill middle with peanut butter. Sprinkle with Rice Krispies.
Enjoy!

title: port diner french dressing
directions: Put in a jar and shake until mixed.
Can be stored in refrigerator for weeks.

title: baked spam
directions: Slice Spam halfway down.
Put onion slice in cut Spam.
Mix catsup, brown sugar and A.1. sauce.
Pour over Spam.
