Bake at 350° until onion is done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream and cream of chicken soup together. Spoon into casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and Ritz crackers. Spread mixture on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with raw veggies: carrots, celery sticks, cauliflower, broccoli, sliced cucumber and green pepper.

title: creamy bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon with onion.
In separate pot, boil vinegar, sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Combine vinegar; mix with bacon, onion and mayonnaise.
Stir until well blended.
Serve hot over spinach or lettuce.

title: easy skillet chops
directions: In a large skillet with lid, put about 1-inch water.
Place well seasoned chops in next.
Add sliced onions and bell pepper. Layer if necessary.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer. Cover.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
No need to stir or rotate unless you wish.
Juices can be thickened and served with boiled spaghetti.

title: peach cooler(non-alcoholic)
directions: Place peaches, honey and a small amount of milk in blender. Puree until almost smooth.
Add remaining milk, ice cream and extract.
Blend until smooth and frothy, about 1 minute.
Serve in tall chilled glasses garnished with fresh peach slices.
Yields 5 glasses.

title: angel's delight
directions: Cut cake into bite size pieces and divide in half.
Line oblong dish with half the cake.
Spread pie filling evenly over top, then add rest of the cake.
Mix sour cream, pudding and milk together until smooth.
Pour over cake top evenly. Chill overnight. Serves about 20.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Cube two slices of the bread and spread it over the bottom of a flat pan or dish.
Mix the next 5 ingredients together and spread over the cubed bread.
Now place four slices of bread over the top of the dish.
Then pour the beaten eggs added to milk over the bread.
Let stand in fridge overnight.
Heat oven to 325°. Pour soup and sliced mushrooms over the souffle.
Bake 1 hour. About ten minutes before taking out of oven, sprinkle shredded cheese over the top and let brown slightly.
Can add a box of frozen peas, if desired.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add spinach, sour cream and next 4 ingredients. Stir well.
Place artichokes in lightly greased casserole.
Spoon spinach mixture over artichokes.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and continue to cook for 10 minutes.

title: italian sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add extract.
Sift baking powder and flour.
Mix well.
Dough should be just firm enough to handle.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Fry in oil until brown and done in center.
Batter should be very thick.

title: thanksgiving dinner
directions: Depending on how far you drive (pack clothes for an overnight trip).
Get up early on Thanksgiving day and go to your mother's house.
If traveling a long distance, use plenty of ingredients 2 and 3. Upon arriving at your destination, prepare your nostrils for some luscious, moth-watering smells.
Help your mother prepare a wonderful dinner (or stay out of the way).
Sit down at the table, say grace and enjoy.
To help make the dinner more enjoyable (especially to your mother) wash the dishes.

title: southwest chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth. Pour into a 13 x 9 inch casserole dish. Mix all other ingredients except Rotel. Pour mixture over rice and top with Rotel. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6. Good with tortilla chips.

title: frosted nuts
directions: Place light brown sugar and water in 2-quart saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to boil. Remove from heat; add nuts and stir mixture until all sugar adheres to nuts.
Cool on waxed paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (don't drain corn) into large casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.
Stir once every 30 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, crumble and set aside.
Reserve three tablespoons bacon drippings in the pan.
Discard remaining drippings.
Add onion slices to the pan and cook until lightly brown.
Add diced potatoes and water.
Cook over medium heat until the potatoes are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add corn, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until heated through.
Pour into warmed bowls and top each serving with crumbled bacon and a pat of butter.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: refried bean casserole(low-fat)
directions: Spray a 9 x 9-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread refried beans on bottom of pan. Top with salsa, chopped onion and ground meat. Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lamb stew with lima or string beans
directions: Cut lamb meat into 2-inch chunks.
Brown slightly and season with salt and pepper.
Add sliced onions and cook until meat is somewhat tender, stirring frequently.
Add string beans or lima beans, whichever you prefer.
Add tomatoes cut into chunks.
Add cold water so stew is juicy.
Cover and cook over medium low heat for 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir and then continue to cook until the beans are done, about 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: water cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients, then add raisins and walnuts. Boil, then let cool.
When cool, add the flour and soda.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: jello punch
directions: Borrow the butter. Borrow the eggs. Borrow the milk. Ask a neighbor if she will bake it in her oven.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°. Divide the pastry in half and roll out 1 half with a floured rolling pin to fit a deep dish, measuring approximately 11 x 8 x 2-inches. Roll out remaining pastry very thin and cut into 1-inch wide strips. Place half of the strips on an ungreased baking sheet and bake until partially cooked and slightly browned. Increase the oven temperature to 425°.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown the ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Mix parsley flakes, eggs, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese together.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer noodles, meat and cheese mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: one dish meal
directions: Make beef into meat balls and brown.
Add potatoes (cut in half), carrots (cut in 1-inch pieces), onions, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours in covered pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except biscuits.
Place in oblong baking dish (10 x 8-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Place biscuits on top and continue baking until browned.

title: marinated steak
directions: Score steak in a crisscross pattern on both sides.
Combine remaining ingredients in a shallow dish.
Marinate steak, covered, overnight.
Turn occasionally; grill or broil until cooked as desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Peel figs and sprinkle sugar on figs (this will allow the figs to produce their own water).
Add jello to figs.
After figs become tender, mash them and boil for 15 to 20 minutes, then place preserves in jars and seal or place them in freezable containers and place in freezer.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend the margarine, Crisco and sugars until fluffy.
Stir in the eggs and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients; mix well.
Spray a cookie sheet with Pam.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto the cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add rest of ingredients; stir until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut into squares.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute green beans in small amount of bacon grease.
Drain. Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish; bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Add one can French fried onions and return to oven and brown.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a large pot, boil potatoes approximately 30 minutes or until soft. Drain water and mash potatoes with margarine and enough milk to make a creamy texture. Set aside.

title: aunt jo's caramel squares
directions: Melt
oleo
and
sugar.
Stir
until creamy and smooth. Cool, then
add other ingredients.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, not a second longer.

title: athenian orzo with shrimp(serves 5)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour and syrup.
Add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry-raspberry salad
directions: Thaw and drain raspberries.
Measure liquid from berries and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Heat liquid and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Whip cranberry sauce and add sour cream.
Blend well.
Add Jell-O mixture and mix well.
Chill until firm.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix other ingredients except peaches.
Pour batter over margarine; then pour peaches over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed, then add Cool Whip to pudding and mix by hand.
Using a 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan, a layer of crackers first, then a layer of pudding mixture, a layer of crackers and repeat ending with crackers.
Spread frosting on top.
Keep refrigerated and let frosting cool before eating.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large bowl, combine coconut, condensed milk and extracts; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto aluminum foil lined and generously greased baking sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes or until lightly brown around edges.
Immediately remove from baking sheet (macaroons will stick if allowed to cool). Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: barry goldwater's arizona chili
directions: Saute beef and drain off fat, leaving a little for flavor. Add beans and onion and stir well.
Mix the chili powder, cumin and salt (about 2 teaspoons to taste) and add to chili.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Turn to low and cook slowly until onion and beans are tender, adding water to desired consistency as needed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cube chicken breasts.

Combine salt substitute, lemon pepper and cornstarch and dredge cubed chicken breasts in the mixture. Saute chicken breasts in canola oil (use your own judgment as to the amount needed) in two batches.
Set aside.
Slice and quarter onions and minced garlic and saute.
Slice and quarter the red and green peppers and saute with onion and garlic.
Drain pineapple and add to onion, garlic and peppers.
If mixture seems dry, add a little of the pineapple juice; reserve the remainder.
Add chicken.
Add soy sauce, vinegar, and sweet basil to taste; add almonds.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook for about 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: polenta (italian corn meal dish)
directions: Add corn meal gradually to boiling water; cook, stirring frequently, for 30 minutes or until thickened.
Add butter and mix well.
Pour onto platter and shape into a ring.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Tomato sauce with meat or chicken cacciatore can be spooned into center of ring.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate chile
directions: Just before serving your favorite hot chile recipe, add one square of chocolate for each quart of finished chile.
Stir vigorously (it will rise).
No one will guess that the distinctly Mexican flavor is chocolate.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Place parboiled chicken breasts in long casserole dish; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place cheese on top of chicken; mix soup with a little water, then pour soup over chicken.
Add already cooked stuffing on top of chicken.
Spread evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until stuffing is lightly brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add jello to boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar and cranberry juice; stir until dissolved.
Chill in refrigerator until partly set.
Fold in drained pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Pour in mold.
Chill until firm.

title: irish soda bread(for two loaves)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add raisins or currants and caraway seed.
Stir in combined melted margarine, beaten eggs and buttermilk until a soft dough is formed.
Turn out on a lightly floured board and knead until stickiness disappears.
Form in two round cake pans (greased).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Saute butter and onions.
Layer pasta, cheese and mashed potatoes, then repeat layers, adding small amount of butter between layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 3 beans and hamburger dish
directions: Fry bacon; brown hamburger and onions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add rice and cook until brown.
Pour into casserole.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook covered tightly at 400° for 1 hour.

title: whipped cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and let stand overnight.
Cut seeded grapes into small pieces.
Fold all the ingredients into whipped cream.
Let stand for 2 to 3 hours.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until it stands in soft peaks. Gradually mix in brown sugar and vanilla. Fold in pecans. Place pecan halves on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes. Turn off oven and let set for 30 minutes. Store in airtight container. Freeze and serve as needed.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar and powdered sugar.
Add Egg Beaters (egg substitute) and mix well.
Blend in cooking oil (Canola) and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done. Remove from baking sheets.
Yield: 6 dozen (2-inch) cookies.
Each cookie contains: 79 calories; 4 grams fat; 45 mg. sodium and no cholesterol.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 cup onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake uncovered 5 minutes longer; also add onions on top with cheese.

title: creole peanut butter soup(a creole style southern favorite)
directions: Saute minced onion in butter for about 3 minutes.
Stir in flour
and seasonings.
Blend in peanut butter.
Gradually stir in	milk.
Cook,
stirring	until thickened.
Add tomato juice and bring
to a boil.	Sprinkle with parsley.	Yields 4 servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Beat eggs together.
Add oil and beat again.
Add flour mixture, then pumpkin and beat well.
Pour into lightly greased and floured pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes for 9-inch pans.

title: frito casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and drain. Pour in both cans of soup; let simmer. Line casserole dish with some of the fritos, then pour beef mixture over top. Cover with more fritos, then lay cheese slices over top. Place in oven until cheese melts. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: taco casserole
directions: In
a large skillet, saute onion in butter until golden.
Add ground beef and cook until crumbly.
Discard grease.
Add salt, crushed garlic, tomato sauce, vinegar and chili powder.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Lightly grease a 2 1/2-quart or a 9
x 13-inch casserole dish and cover bottom with 1/3 of the chips.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of cheese, then spoon over 1/2 of the meat mixture.
Add another 1/3 of the cheese and 1/3 of chips, then add remaining meat sauce.
Top with remaining cheese and chips.
(This much can be done ahead; cover and refrigerate.) Mix lettuce with onions and tomatoes and sprinkle over hot casserole. Garnish with sour cream and sliced olives.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs slightly in large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Then stir into egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon butter into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until center springs back.

title: macaroni seafood salad
directions: Rinse, drain and chill macaroni.
Add celery, onion and lobster.
Gently mix in salad dressing and Ranch dressing.

title: jalapeno roll-ups
directions: Combine first four ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Spread on tortillas and roll tightly.
Refrigerate overnight and slice before serving.
"These get hotter as they warm to room temperature."

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop.
Chop other vegetables.
Boil all ingredients, except vinegar, together for two hours, or until soft and broken.
Add vinegar and boil for one hour, stirring frequently.
Put in jars and seal while hot.

title: stuffed beef shells
directions: Brown ground beef.
Combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce.
Stir 1/2 of chilies, 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/2 can of onions; mix well.
Pour 1/2 of remaining sauce on bottom of a 10-inch round baking dish.
Stuff shells with beef mixture.
Top with remaining cheese and chilies.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: play doh
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until you can't stir anymore. Remove from heat and pour onto wax paper.
Knead until completely cool.
Store in airtight plastic container.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix half of the cake mix (dry), margarine, brown sugar, water and eggs in a large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and the nuts. Spread in pan.
Bake 20 minutes. Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed and golden.
Heat frosting in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thin. Drizzle over top.
Cool completely.
Makes 35 squares.

title: island style cracklin' bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Add buttermilk and cracklings;
mix
well.
Shape into patties; place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake
at 450° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: spicy vegetable dip
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Season with remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing just enough to cover ingredients. Serve with tortilla chips or party crackers.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Blend muffin mix, milk and eggs. Add corn, cheese, chilies and salsa. Blend. Spread into lightly buttered iron skillet. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except potato chips.
Put into baking dish.
Sprinkle chips on top.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: In saucepan, combine orange and pineapple juice, sugar, egg and 1 tablespoon lemon juice. Boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Let cool.
When cool, fold in whipping cream.

title: swiss steak with vegetables
directions: Trim fat from steak and cut into serving size pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge steak in mixture and pound into steak with meat mallet.
Brown steak in oil in large skillet. Place in shallow 2-quart casserole.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and cherry juice in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils. Remove from heat and add butter, cherries and lemon juice.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan; cover top with crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Make slits in crust to permit steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 more minutes, or until crust is brown.

title: peanut butter chiffon pie
directions: Bake pie shell. Cool. Combine gelatin, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Add milk.
Slowly add beaten egg yolks. Add peanut butter. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Chill until slightly thickened. Beat egg whites until frothy.

Beat in brown sugar gradually until stiff peaks form. Fold into peanut butter mixture. Fold in whipped topping. Pour into shell. Chill until firm. Garnish with additional whipped topping and shaved chocolate chips.

title: easy cream of potato soup
directions: Cook ingredients until very tender.
Melt 6 tbsp. butter in a large cooker, add 4 tbsp. flour, blend over low heat until bubbly. Stir in 2 c. of milk, add cooked potato mixture.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in drained zucchini. Combine stuffing and butter.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing mixture in bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Melt together butterscotch morsels and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, and add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients to egg mixture and nutmeats if you wish.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while still warm.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine butter, sugar, milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well, then stir in oats.
Spoon out on greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: apple-nut-horseradish dip
directions: Grate apples.
Immediately combine with lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Serve dip at once with chips, crackers or vegetables.
Makes almost 1 cup.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding with 2 1/2 cups of milk.
Separately, mix sugar, margarine and cream cheese together.
Combine with pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of new flowerpot with foil.
Using a food processor, put Oreos in, a few at a time, until fine with the appearance of dirt.
Begin layers with Oreos, pudding mix, etc., ending with Oreos on top.
Can garnish with silk flowers for centerpiece.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In large bowl, mix the cream cheese, sour cream, salad dressing, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and garlic salt until smooth.
Add enough milk to make mixture creamy.
Stir in 2 tablespoons grated cheese.
Fold crab meat into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° until mixture is bubbly and browned on top, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Great with Ritz crackers.

title: marinated salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Slice other vegetables, except olives.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour over ham when ready to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Measure and sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir until well mixed. Stir in mashed bananas.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Put in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or an 8-inch square pan. Bake at 325° or 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Arrange chicken in 8 x 4 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drizzle butter over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Place cooked and drained broccoli around chicken.
Blend soup, milk and cheese; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Yields 4 servings.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in buttermilk.
Combine flour, cornmeal, salt, paprika and black pepper in brown paper bag.
Put chicken in bag and shake to coat.
Do this 1 hour ahead of cooking time for coating to set.
Heat oil and fry 30 or 40 minutes until done. Handle chicken as little as possible while frying.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Take out of freezer 15 minutes before using.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: bear cub cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients except rice krispies and oatmeal.
Stir them in after ingredients are mixed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork slightly.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
While hot sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: busy day cabbage rolls
directions: Melt shortening; add onions, meat, salt and pepper; brown. Add cooked rice.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan or any baking dish.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix. Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: easy reindeer cookies
directions: Freeze dough 15 minutes.
Cut dough into 30 (1/4-inch thick) slices.
Place 4-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Using thumb and forefinger, pinch in each slice about 2/3 of the way down to shape face.
Press a pretzel on each side of larger end for antlers.
Press in chocolate morsels for eyes.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and press in red candy M&M's for nose.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yields approximately 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fruit cups
directions: Make pie crust and line cupcake tins.
Cut up dates, cherries and nuts.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and eggs.
Pour over dates, cherries and nuts until nearly full.
Bake at 375°.

title: easy pizza bagels
directions: Cut bagels in half.
Place on cookie sheet.
Spread pizza sauce on top of bagels.
Add toppings of your choice.
Spread shredded cheese on top.
Bake in a 400° oven until cheese melts. Great for after school snacks, lunch or slumber party treats.

title: angel punch
directions: Chill juice and nectar almost to a freeze.
Combine remaining ingredients in punch bowl.
Can be decorated with 1 small jar maraschino cherries, drained. Makes about 20 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: never fail hot rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar, salt and shortening to melt shortening. Cool.
Add this to 2 cups of the flour.
Add egg and beat well. In separate container, dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon of sugar in water.
Add this to first mixture and beat until small bubbles form.
Then fold in 2 more cups of sifted flour.
Mix well with spoon, dough will be very soft.
Might need to add a little flour to be able to handle.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use (overnight).
Remove from fridge and cover; let it rise once in a warm place, about 2 hours.
Then roll and make into your turnovers or just plain rolls.
I let these rise about 2 hours in warm kitchen.
Cook at 400° about 15 to 20 minutes or until well browned.
You can make this early in the morning and use for dinner that night.
Makes 36.

title: mexican style cream of chicken
directions: In a 6 to 8-quart kettle, combine the whole chicken, water and onions.
Cover; bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce to medium and simmer until meat pulls easily from bones, about 1 hour.

title: melanzane marinade
directions: Slice eggplant in 3 centimeter thick slices.
(Optional:
Peel eggplant.)
Sprinkle with salt, cover and let stand 30 minutes. Discard water which comes from eggplant and dry with paper towels. Saute eggplant with garlic and olive oil.
Press and cook garlic in a small amount of olive oil.
Cut hot pepper into thin strips. Place vinegar, garlic, hot pepper, black pepper and laurel leaf in a small pot and boil.
Pour mixture over vegetables, cover and let sit for half a day in a cold place.
Top with remaining ingredients and serve cold or at room temperature.
Serve as a side dish with meat.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water; stir in pineapple.
Place sliced bananas on the top; cover with marshmallows.
Refrigerate to let jello stiffen.

title: haystacks
directions: Place chocolate in top of double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir until chocolate is smooth.
Add pretzels and peanuts to melted chocolate and stir until well coated with chocolate.
Pour into buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, spreading to edges of pan.
Chill 20 minutes or until firm.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Make hamburger patties; mix with bread crumbs, egg, seasoning and ground beef; form and pan-fry.
Put cooked patties into crock-pot; cover with diluted ketchup.
Add sliced green pepper (and onions, if desired, but not necessary).
Simmer at least 3 to 4 hours.

title: french-style potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool slightly; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Add wines; toss gently.
Let stand 10 minutes and combine.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all vegetables.
Combine other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Good with barbecue!

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Steam squash, onion and pepper for 10 minutes.
Put in bowl and mix vegetables, crumbs, eggs and margarine.
Put into greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tea
directions: Add tea bags and sugar to water in medium size pot.
Bring to boil, then turn heat down to medium.
Let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let mixture cool, then add enough cold water to make 1 gallon.

title: potato cheddar chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan combine potatoes, onion, salt and water. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes; set aside (do not drain).
In another medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually add milk; blend until smooth.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Add undrained vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat; do not boil.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Yields 5 cups.

title: snow ball cake
directions: Soften unflavored gelatin in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar and lemon juice. Add canned pineapple and juice; chill mixture until partly firm. Whip 2 packages Dream Whip and fold into partly set mixture.
Use 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place layer of cake, then layer of gelatin mixture; repeat layers until all is used.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Then whip 1 package Dream Whip and spread on cake; cover with coconut.
Trim with cherries.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; mix with oil and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients together and then add vanilla.
Mix all together and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soup and pepper.
Pour over beans.
Add 1/2 onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: crepes with ham(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Sift flour and salt and place in a blender.
Add eggs.
Use the blender at low speed and add butter and milk, beating until the batter is the consistency of thick cream.
Let batter stand for 1 hour before baking.

title: broccoli stir-fry with garlic
directions: Lightly spray a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Add garlic and cook on medium-high until soft, about 30 seconds. Stir in broccoli cuts and cook for 1 minute.
Add lemon juice and broth.
Stir-fry broccoli until tender-crisp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple-carrot-raisin salad
directions: Prepare fruit and vegetables.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Add some pineapple juice, if desired.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8, as fruit cup, salad for light snack or dessert.
Very colorful and easy salad.

title: egg rolls (lumpia)
directions: Saute garlic and onions in oil.
When garlic is brown and onion is transparent, add celery, carrots and green beans.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown meat, onion and spices.
Blend in pizza sauce.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes. Serve with salad.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
In a separate bowl, make a paste with cocoa and food coloring.
Add to oil, sugar, and eggs.
Put flour in sifter and add salt.
Take buttermilk and add a little flour and blend.
Add a little buttermilk and continue until all four is mixed.
Mix vinegar and soda.
Add to mixture last.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage - egg casserole(breakfast casserole)
directions: Crumble and brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Mix with rice.
Layer rice, krispies, sausage mixture and cheese in a lasagne pan.
Continue until you have used up mixture.
Beat 6 eggs with the 2 can of cream of celery soup, pour over the casserole.
Bake 350 for 40 minutes.

title: light 'n fruity pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whisk, blend in Cool Whip; beat until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill mixture until it will mound, about 15 minutes.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours or freeze until smooth.
Excellent with orange gelatin; tastes like a creamsicle.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Mix together.
Take 1/2 cup for top.
Pat rest in bottom of pan.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into large bowl.
Cut in Crisco.
Add egg.
Add extract.
Roll dough in tiny balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each ball with tip of baby finger.
Dot each depression with red food coloring.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken crepes
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Combine eggs and milk.
Stir into flour mixture.
Blend in melted butter.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Brush bottom of 6 or 7-inch heavy skillet with salad oil.
Place over medium heat until hot, not smoking.
Pour 2 tablespoons batter in pan.
Quickly tilt pan in all directions so batter covers pan (thin film).
Cook about 1 minute.
Flip.
Cook about 30 seconds. Place hot crepe on towel to cool.
Stack crepes between layers of waxed paper.
Yields 30 to 32.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients in a bowl. Put chicken in 13 x 9 x 2 casserole dish. Pour cranberry mixture over chicken. Bake 1 hour (or more if needed) at 350° (uncovered).

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour and soda together; set aside. Add 1/4 teaspoon salt to egg whites and beat until stiff peaks form; set aside.
Mix margarine, sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and beat well after each one.
Add flour mixture, a little at a time.
Alternate with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Fold in egg whites and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: rocky road pie
directions: Pour water over Grape-Nuts.
Let set until cool.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt, butter, syrup and flavoring.
Add Grape-Nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes until set.

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: You can add beans of your choice, if you wish too.

title: broiled venison, elk or antelope steaks or chops
directions: Preheat
broiler.
Rub	steaks	or
chops
with garlic. Brush meat with
mixture of butter or olive oil, salt, pepper, paprika and
Worcestershire
sauce.
Broil	at least 3-inches away from heat for
8 to 10 minutes on each side or to desired doneness. Serve with currant jelly or spicy sauce.

title: hershey's bar pie
directions: Melt hershey's bars, cool slightly. Stir in cool whip and pour into pie crust. Chill several hours. Serve cold.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls onto pizza pan and bake according to directions on the can.
Spread cream cheese over pizza while still warm.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and ranch dressing mix. Spread on top of pizza.
Cut vegetables up into bite-size pieces. Place on top of pizza, then top with Cheddar cheese.
Keep refrigerated until ready to eat.

title: celeste's  favorite oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over large box of oyster crackers and toss to coat thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Best to make the day before using so the flavors will blend.

title: sugared date squares
directions: Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In a large saucepan, combine brown sugar, margarine and dates.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture is smooth, about 5 minutes. Stir in vanilla, cereal and nuts.
Spread in prepared pan.
Cool completely.
Cut cooled bars into 1-inch squares.
Coat all sides with powdered sugar.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: peach cobbler 2
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan; place peaches in bottom of pan and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Combine butter, egg and milk; stir in sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Spoon batter evenly over peaches; bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.

title: beef salad provencale
directions: *Or use 1 (12 ounce) can chopped beef.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello, hot water and pineapple juice; chill until partially set.
Mix cranberries and sugar.
Add celery, pineapple and nuts.
After jello is partly chilled, add first mixture and let jell.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs.
Beat well after each addition. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately to butter mixture. Stir in dates, orange slices and chopped nuts.
This makes a very stiff dough. Bake in small loaf pan to serve with tea or punch.

title: fancy baked chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Melt margarine.
Blend together the margarine, cheese and salts.
Dip each piece in the mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish and pour remaining margarine mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: potato-vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, peel and dice potatoes.
Combine all other ingredients.
Toss and serve.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Add to other recipe ingredients in portions listed.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening. Cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg. Beat well.

title: pilaf with tomatoes and peppers
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Cover tightly; microwave on High (100%) for 8 minutes.
Stir.
If rice is not tender, cover and microwave an additional 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef taco salad
directions: In medium skillet, fry ground beef and onion; drain off fat. Add taco seasoning and mix well.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Set out ice cream to get soft.
Crush up Oreo cookies and mix with oleo.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch pan to make a crust.
Spread softened ice cream on top of Oreo cookie crust and put in freezer until ice cream is frozen.
Pour jar of chocolate fudge over ice cream.
Put Cool Whip over chocolate fudge.
Decorate with crushed nuts or leftover cookie crumbs.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.

title: enchiladas
directions: Wrap tortillas in damp towel and put in oven to steam for 15 minutes at 350°.
Open shells and layer with hamburger, then onion and cheese.
Put Velveeta, soup, chillies and milk in double boiler and heat through.
Pour over top of tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blushin russian
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: coventry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, mix lard, 1 cup packed brown sugar and egg yolks until blended.
Reduce speed to low; beat in flour, buttermilk, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, vanilla extract, nutmeg and cloves until blended.
Spoon into baking dish.
In small bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually sprinkle in 1 cup packed brown sugar until sugar dissolves.
Spread meringue over unbaked cake batter, covering top completely.
Arrange pecan halves in 3 rows of 5 pecans each.
Bake cake 40 to 45 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: simple vegetable soup
directions: Place zucchini, onion, carrots and celery in a pot.
Add chicken broth just to cover vegetables.
Add thyme and basil and simmer until vegetables are soft, about 45 minutes.
Allow soup to cool slightly.
Puree in blender, about 2 cups at a time.
Makes 5 servings.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter with granulated and brown sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt and blend into the creamed mixture to make a smooth dough.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place in ungreased miniature muffin tins.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

Have miniature peanut butter cups ready, papers removed. Immediately after removing trays from oven, press a peanut butter cup into the center of each hot cookie until only the top of the candy shows.
Let cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes before removing the cookies to a tray for serving or to an airtight container for storage.

title: salmon spread supreme
directions: In a medium bowl, blend salmon, cream cheese, onions, lemon juice, horseradish and salt.
Wrap in wax paper to form a ball. Chill one hour or until firm. Roll in parsley and nuts; chill until ready to use.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, shortening and sour milk.
Mix until smooth.
Add boiling water and vanilla; mix well. Pour into layer pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Shape about 16 meat balls from first 4 ingredients and brown in shortening; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Stir now and then.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Nice for breakfast or snacks.
Spread with orange marmalade for a treat.

title: deer meat and gravy
directions: Cover meat with water.
Add Creole seasoning.
Place meat in crock-pot.
Cook on high all day.

title: sunday morning venison stew
directions: Spray a medium to large baking dish with a nonstick spray. Place venison in baking dish; slice onion on top of venison.
Mix mushrooms with cream of mushroom soup; spread mixture over meat and onion.
Cover; cook at 275° for 3 hours.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Combine milk, pineapple and lemonade in bowl; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping and desired amount of food coloring.
Pour into pie shell and chill for several hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: italian ice
directions: Put water and lemonade drink into blender.
Cover.
Liquify, with motor running.
Remove feeder cap and add ice cubes until slushy.

title: elfin cheesecake
directions: Beat the cheese until smooth and gradually beat in the sugar. Blend the remaining ingredients until smooth.
Add your favorite topping and chill.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well and
bake
in
unbaked pie shell for 1 hour at 350°.

title: foolproof fish
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in shallow baking dish in 450° oven until butter is browned.
Place fillets, flesh side down, in sizzling butter and bake for 5 to 10 minutes. Turn over and baste with butter in pan.
Sprinkle each fillet with lemon juice, wine, Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until done.
Broil briefly until lightly browned.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple nut torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg with electric beater until light and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into the egg mixture.
Stir in apples, walnuts and vanilla.
Butter the inside of an 8 x 8-inch pan and pour in batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: frosting
directions: Mix and spread over cake when cool.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 36 (1 x 2-inch) bars.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix into Cool Whip. Add crushed pineapple (do not drain). Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Garnish with additional cherries and marshmallows, if desired.
Serves 10.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon. Into a bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Gradually stir in oil, lightly beaten eggs, orange juice and vanilla.
Beat the mixture until smooth.
Pour half the mixture into a well buttered Bundt pan.
Arrange half the apple slices on top of batter and sprinkle them lightly with half the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Add the remaining batter; top it with the remaining apple slices and sprinkle the cake with the rest of the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake cake in a moderately slow oven at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until it tests done.
Let the cake cool in the pan for 15 minutes.
Invert it on a cake rack and let it cool completely.
Ovens vary; your cake may be done in 1 hour.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and butter; mix well.
Heat until starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal; mix well.

title: yum, yum cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed on package but add 1 1/3 cups coconut to the batter.
Bake and let cool.
Beat the cream cheese, adding the 2 cups milk and the pudding mix.
Continue beating on low speed for 2 minutes. Add the remaining 1 cup coconut.
Spread this mixture over the cooled cake.
Drain the can of crushed pineapple and spoon the drained pineapple over the top of the cream cheese mixture. Spread 1 container Cool Whip as final topping and chill.
Makes about 20 pieces. Yum, Yum!

title: large pita(easter bread)
directions: Boil anise seed and water for 5 minutes; let stand (if you use anise seed instead of anise extract).
Scald milk.
Add sugar to milk.
If the mix should cool before using, reheat it.
Put butter in pan.
Add eggs, then add milk-sugar mixture.
Crumble yeast and add warm anise juice or water to milk, then add flour.
Put in pan and grease top with oil.
Let raise about 2 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk, then knead and raise again.
Regrease top. Grease bottom of pans.
Divide dough and shape into loaves.
Let raise in pans for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Beat eggs and brush tops. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 250° for 55 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy chocolate crescents
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan melt chocolate bars over low heat, stirring often.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in dessert topping (mixture will thicken).
Cover and chill thoroughly at least 1 hour.
Form into 1 inch balls or crescent shapes.
Roll in vanilla crumbs.
Chill thoroughly.
Store covered and in fridge.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, shortening, water and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to mixture.
Mix well, then add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful or tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until done in a 375° oven.

title: leftover special
directions: Mix roast, vegetables and liquid in a casserole.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are golden brown.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in 1-quart casserole and cover.
Microwave at 100% power 5 minutes.
Stir well. Microwave, uncovered, at 100% power until a hard ball forms when a small amount is dropped in cold water, 4 to 6 minutes.
Cool 3 to 4 minutes.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Pour sugar mixture in a steady stream over egg whites, beating constantly until mixture holds its shape and starts to lose its gloss.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: taco dinner(kid's stuff)
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Put in a bowl.
Shred Velveeta.
Put in a bowl.
Cut tomato.
Put in a bowl.
Make hot sauce.
Put in a bowl.
Shred lettuce.
Put in a bowl.
Cook taco until brown.
Cook in oven for 3 minutes at 200°.

title: honey-walnut chicken
directions: Cut breast meat into strips or nugget-size bites. Melt half a stick of butter. Dip chicken into melted butter and cover with crumbs. Place in greased casserole dish. Add a little butter to dish. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes. Heat honey and about 1 teaspoon of butter, mixing well. When chicken is done, sprinkle nuts over the chicken and pour honey mixture over it.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Mix sugar, buttermilk and soda.
Cook to hard boil stage for candy.
Remove from fire; add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Spoon out on buttered wax paper quickly.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Whip together whipping cream, sugar and cream cheese.
Pour into pie crust and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Cool and spread with blueberry jam.
Top with blueberries.
Spread whipped cream over top.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add taco seasoning and Hidden Valley dressing. Put in 5-quart Dutch oven and add chiles, tomatoes, hominy and beans.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chinese tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine tuna, celery, onions, soup, water and Chinese noodles in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cashews.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: anise tea(shai bi yansoon)
directions: Steep anise seed in boiling water 10 minutes.
Strain and add anise water to the 2 cups hot tea.
Serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp and crabmeat spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crabmeat, shrimp, green pepper, celery, onion and Miracle Whip in medium bowl.
Spread in glass baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs or cornflake crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Serve on Triscuits.

title: noodles
directions: Mix and let stand 10 minutes. Roll out and let stand 20 minutes. Cut and let dry for 2 hours.
Makes 3 cups.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix well and bake in a buttered casserole at 325° for 40 minutes or until firm.
Do not overbake.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in large bowl sugar and flour.
Mix in saucepan cocoa, oil, margarine and water.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Pour hot mixture over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs and soda.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice.
Put in jars with 2 garlic buds and 2 heads of dill.
Heat vinegar mixture and pour over pickles. Cold pack for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: graham cracker bear party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve immediately.

title: spicy punch
directions: Add boiling water to tea bags, cinnamon sticks and cloves. Steep 10 minutes. Remove tea bags and add sugar and all juices and cider. Heat just to boiling, stirring to blend. Remove cloves.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together chicken, vegetables, tomatoes and onion soup.
Place in a casserole dish.
Cut canned biscuits into fourths and place on top of mixture to form a "crust."
Bake for about 45 minutes.

title: maple memory cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Cream shortening, gradually add brown sugar and cream well.
Add egg and maple flavoring.
Beat well and add maple syrup.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture, blending well.
Add chopped walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Top with half walnut.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown in 350° oven.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: Cook pasta and set aside. Heat oil over low heat. Add chicken, onions and peppers. Cook until chicken is no longer pink and vegetables are tender. Stir in soup-water, pasta and mixed thawed vegetables. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes. Makes about 4 servings.

title: sue's antipasto salad
directions: Dice or chop all of the ingredients, except macaroni.
Add to cooked macaroni.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar. Beat until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk. Add food coloring, vanilla and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Gently fold in the berries.
Spread in a greased 11 x 7 x 21.5-inch pan.
Top with berries.

title: beth's mexican salsa
directions: In a large bowl, squish tomatoes; combine with the rest of the ingredients.
This is best when prepared 24 hours ahead.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and set aside.
Prepare rice and mix with broccoli.
Add jar of Cheez Whiz and can of soup (undiluted).
Mix well.
Add onions as desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat with onions.
Add celery and broth.
Cook until celery is tender.
Add 3 cups water and bouillon cubes. Simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and other vegetables.
Heat for 15 minutes.
Ready to serve!

title: veal and peppers
directions: Brown meat in 3 tablespoons oil. Add sauce and seasonings, stir.
Add the vegetables, cover and cook until meat is white and tender.
Uncover last 15 minutes.
Add wine.
Serve on noodles, rice or side dish with potatoes.

title: peanut pinto bean pie
directions: Mash cooked beans.
Combine sugar, salt and flour.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Add oleo, vanilla, coconut and peanuts. Pour
into unbaked
9-inch
pie
shell.
Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mints
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add a little more water if needed.
Mixture should be stiff.
Roll into tiny balls and press flat, about 1/4-inch.
Cut any shape you like.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cream sugar and egg together.
Add milk and stir.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to mixture.
Stir well. Pour into 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole with onions
directions: Mix vegetables, soup, cheese and mayonnaise with half of the onions.
Place in casserole dish; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions; return to oven until onions are golden brown (approximately 5 minutes).

title: carrot soup
directions: In soup pot, saute onion and garlic in margarine until soft. Stir in thyme.
Mix in carrots, potatoes, bay leaf and pepper. Add chicken bouillon cubes and enough water to cover.
Bring soup to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf and puree soup in blender (small amount at a time). Serve hot or lukewarm.
Makes 11 (1 cup) servings.

title: chicken breast alfredo
directions: Coat chicken breasts with flour.
Set aside.
Combine egg, water, Romano cheese, parsley and salt.
Mix well.
Dip flour coated chicken into egg mixture.
Roll chicken breasts in seasoned bread crumbs.
Heat butter and oil in large skillet and fry chicken until golden brown.
Cook slowly 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove to baking dish.
When ready to bake, top each piece of chicken with a piece of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour cheese sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve immediately. Can be done a day ahead, but don't put cheese on.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake following box directions.
Cool and cut down through middle of cake.

title: joe joe's mac and tuna dinner
directions: Cook macaroni and

cheese dinner according to package directions. Heat sweet peas in microwave or on stove top until tender. In large bowl or casserole, mix macaroni and cheese, peas and tuna together. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top, if desired.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours (do not freeze).
Top with chilled cherry or blueberry pie filling.
Serve.

title: grandma dellar's pickled beets
directions: You will need canning jars, lids and rings for this recipe.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar and corn syrup together in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Stir. Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir until light and foamy.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Work fast because it hardens quickly.
If you wish, you can substitute 7 ounces almonds and 1 teaspoon almond extract (for vanilla) or 1 cup pecans or 7 ounces cashews.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.
Cut thin slice off top of each potato.
Scoop out pulp.
Put pulp in bowl.
Add egg yolks and stir until smooth.
Add butter and cream. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into potato mixture.
Fill shells with mixture. Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let stand at room temperature until soft enough to beat with mixer.
Blend well.
Return to refrigerator until firm enough to shape into balls.
Roll balls in crushed walnuts.
Keep in refrigerator.
These freeze well.

title: quick pizza dough
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Let raise until twice as high.
Oil 2 pizza pans lightly.
Spread dough on tins.
Pour on your favorite sauce, cheese and whatever else you would like.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 9-inch pan, mix rhubarb, jello and sugar. Mix cake mix, oleo and sprinkle on rhubarb.
Pour water over all.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool slightly and refrigerate until firm.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until vegetables are done.
Can be eaten any time.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: *You can also use a combination of jalapenos, banana or bell pepper.

title: turkey or chicken cream stew
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Add milk and broth; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Add all other ingredients; heat thoroughly.
Pour over hot biscuits, noodles or rice.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix all together and freeze overnight.
Can use cherry pie filling.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Gradually add coconut and blend well, then gradually add sugar and mix completely.
Roll into balls and coat with cinnamon.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in 2 cups water until tender.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Cook onion in drippings.
Add crumbled bacon and onion to potatoes.
Blend milk and flour; add to potatoes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Stir lemonade and condensed milk.
Fold in one large Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill one hour before serving.

title: australian jack
directions: Warm fat sufficiently to rub into oats.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Press into flat pan.
Bake at 400° until golden, about 30 minutes.

title: pepper sauce
directions: Cut open all of the peppers and remove seeds.

Roll the same peppers together in foil. Grill them for 15 minutes. Unwrap the foil from around the peppers and drain off any water. Put all the peppers in a blender and blend until liquefied. Put liquid in a pot and add half a cup of water. Bring to a boil and add salt to your taste. Very hot sauce.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, blend together eggs, cooking oil and prunes.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in tube pan 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crushed pecans.
Form into balls and chill.
Roll in the crushed pecans.
Serve with cinnamon crisp crackers.

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Trim crusts and flatten bread with a rolling pin.
Cream egg yolks, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread generously on each slice of bread and roll up.
Brush rolls with melted butter and roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture, coating well.
Freeze.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Do not thaw before baking.

title: tia's perfect pizza
directions: Warm water to about 110° to 115°.
Pour into a bowl and dissolve yeast.
Quickly add flour, cup by cup and add olive oil and salt.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Put dough in a lightly greased bowl, cover and let rise for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 large or 2 (12-inch) pizzas.
Top with your favorite sauce, spices and meats or vegetables.
Bake about 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown in an oven at 450°.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Boil
the
first 4 ingredients, without stirring, until soft ball
stage.
Add
vanilla	and nuts. Stir until nuts are well covered.
Place on wax paper and separate when cool.

title: richard's slaw
directions: Grind or shred cabbage.
Grate carrots.
Stir together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and let set in refrigerator for several hours or overnight to let flavors blend.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: In large saucepan,
bring water and bouillon cubes to a boil. Add noodles; cook uncovered until tender (10 minutes).
Add soup and sour cream.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar well and pour over vegetables. Mix until well coated.
Refrigerate.
Increase or decrease dressing according to amount of vegetables.

title: festive cheese balls
directions: Blend cheeses, pineapple, sauce and scallions.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Shape into balls and roll in chopped pecans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and grate cheese.
Mix broccoli, soup, cheese, mayonnaise, egg and onion together in large bowl.
Place in greased casserole dish and top with almonds and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter. Add ripe bananas and eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to batter.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bran whole wheat muffins
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Then add flour, baking powder and salt.
Bake at 400 for 20 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: chinese hot dish
directions: Mix the soup, mushrooms and 1 cup chow mein noodles with the first 3 ingredients.
Add the soy sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add 1/2 cup chow mein noodles on top the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: escalloped broccoli and corn
directions: Combine all 8 items in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with
buttered
Ritz
cracker crumbs (16 crackers).
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chunky vegetarian chili
directions: Saute pepper, onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in all the other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer, cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes, until rice is cooked.

title: neiman marcus cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla extract. Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 50+ cookies.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine cream cheese with unbeaten eggs.
Add sugar and salt; beat well.
Add semi-sweet chocolate chips.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat on low speed until blended, then on medium speed for two minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine egg, salt and milk.
Add 1 cup flour or enough to make dough stiff.
Roll very thin on floured surface and let stand 20 minutes.
Roll up loosely and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Spread out and let dry 2 hours.
Drop into boiling soup or salted water and cook, uncovered, about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 cups cooked noodles.

title: veggie pie
directions: Drain meat.
Roll out dough on greased baking sheet.
Fill with meat and cheese.
Roll out rest of dough on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: Mix well and press into large Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients, tossing lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with rotary or electric mixer at medium speed. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until filling is set and top is golden brown.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chip-peanut butter cookie
directions: Mix white sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, oleo, eggs and vanilla. Add soda dissolved in hot water. Add oats and chocolate chips. Mix well. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Remove from pans.

title: ginger ale chili
directions: Saute first four ingredients for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Add tomatoes, ginger ale, wine, Worcestershire, salt and pepper and cook 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days. Serve with Cheddar cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients, simmer 20 minutes, uncovered. Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Makes 1 3/4 cups. Recipe may be doubled.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Heat bacon in heavy, large skillet until small amount of fat begins to accumulate.
Add cabbage and continue cooking over very low heat, stirring frequently, until cabbage is tender and starts to turn golden brown.
Stir in cream and lemon juice.
Heat until cream is hot.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Beat the Cool Whip, pudding and milk all together.
Put graham crackers, then half of filling, graham crackers and rest of filling.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: In small saucepan, melt chocolate with butter or margarine over low heat, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Karo syrup and milk.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set out cheeses to soften overnight.
Blend cheeses together with a mixer.
Add other ingredients, and mix well.
Make into 2 balls.
Coat with finely chopped pecans and parsley flakes.

title: karrer fricassee
directions: Fillet breasts.
In large skillet saute garlic in butter.
Coat chicken with flour and add to hot pan.
Brown chicken.
Cut lemon into quarters and squeeze over chicken.
Add wine gradually; salt and pepper.
Cook chicken 4 minutes each side.
Cut top of scallions into dice-size pieces.
Add last couple of minutes of cooking to chicken.
Simmer another 2 to 3 minutes.
Add juice of another quartered lemon.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add remaining wine, 1/4 teaspoon of butter and 1 teaspoon of minced garlic and simmer on medium heat, adding heavy cream.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll in nuts.

title: tomato pesto with pasta and shrimp
directions: In bowl, mix pesto, thyme, zest, salt, pepper and lemon juice; add shrimp and parsley.
Cook pasta until done.
Add 1/2 cup pasta water to pesto mixture; mix until blended.
Drain pasta; add and toss.
Serves 4.
Contains 562 calories and 27 grams fat.

title: heavenly coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
While hot, poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake and let cool. Mix Cool Whip and one small can cream of coconut.
Spread on cake and top with coconut.
Refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Add all ingredients in large saucepan.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 hours.

title: "mom's punch"
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, lemonade, sugar and water.
Add pineapple juice and frozen orange juice.
Right before serving, add orange sherbet, then slowly pour in Sprite, causing sherbet to froth. Makes 1 punch bowl full.

title: spoonburger
directions: Brown ground beef, then add carrots, catsup, onion and water. Cover pan and cook slowly until well done.

title: ritzy corn pie
directions: In a bowl, combine crumbs and 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Pour into baking dish and press down.
Cook onions and peppers in rest of margarine until tender.
Blend flour and seasonings.
Add to onions and peppers.
Add in corn.
Stir and cook until thick.
Add eggs and milk to corn mixture.
Add bacon.
Put into crust.
Bake at 375°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: kielbasa and cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl combine brown sugar, orange peel, garlic, salt, nutmeg, pepper and cloves.
In a Dutch oven, arrange in layers half of the cabbage, half of onions and half of apples.
Sprinkle with half of brown sugar mixture.
Top with half of pepper strips.
Repeat.
Pour orange juice over top. Bake, covered, 1 hour.
Make 1/4-inch deep slashes at 2-inch intervals in the kielbasa.
Place in Dutch oven, pressing down to cover the kielbasa with pan juices.
Bake, covered, about 30 minutes longer.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: pico del galo
directions: Combine onions, tomatoes, peppers, cilantro, lime juice, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
In skillet, combine butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Pour over macaroni.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows on High in microwave for 3 minutes. Mix in the Rice Krispies.
Put in greased dish.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in broth until tender.
Cool and cube. Saute onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Just before celery and onion are tender, add mushrooms.
Cook spaghetti in just enough broth to cover.
When done, add cheese to broth and spaghetti. Let cheese melt and thicken.
Mix chicken.
Add all ingredients. Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: chuck wagon mac
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown ground beef.
Add celery, onion, pepper, corn, tomatoes and tomato paste with water.
Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on box.
Mix with beef mixture.
Simmer for about 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand, except bananas and nuts. Stir in bananas and nuts. Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Check cake at 45 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Cut a seam down middle of each chili.
Stuff with cheese.
Whip egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in slightly beaten egg yolks.
Roll chilies in flour. Dip in egg mixture.
Fry to golden brown.
Serve with your favorite chili sauce.

title: the easiest frozen fruit salad
directions: Freeze can of fruit cocktail.
Open both ends of the can; push contents out.
Slice.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with whipped cream or salad dressing.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 to 5 servings.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cook stew meat in bouillon water until tender.
Add cut up onion together with pepper and salt.
Cook for about 15 minutes over medium heat.
Add tomato soup and cook about 10 minutes.
Add carrots, cabbage or lettuce, mixed vegetables and potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Takes about 4 hours to soften until tender.

title: blanche's cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add oleo and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for a few minutes.
Take from heat and add oatmeal, coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper and allow to harden.

title: oriental mushrooms
directions: Saute onion in butter in 10-inch skillet until tender.
Add mushrooms; stir until coated with butter.
Sprinkle with flour. Add water, bouillon and soy sauce; mix well.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add almonds.
Serves 4.

title: peach and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve orange Jell-O according to directions. When cool, pour into long pan and add peaches. Refrigerate until set. Blend cheese with a little pineapple juice. Spread on congealed orange Jell-O. Prepare lime Jell-O. Add crushed pineapple. Pour on top of cream cheese mixture when ready to congeal.

title: creole seafood supreme
directions: Melt cream cheese and 6 tablespoons butter in the top of a double boiler or microwave oven.
Set aside.
Saute green onions, bell pepper and celery in remaining 2 tablespoons butter until tender; add shrimp.
Saute until pink.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry hamburger - mix with remaining ingredients except cheese. Place in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until bubbling through.

title: fried pig feet
directions: Clean pig feet under water, scraping feet with edge of knife, careful to check for hair between toes.
Soak in the salt water overnight.
Boil feet until tender, which could take hours.
Let cool.
Cut feet in half between toes.
You should have 2 equal halves.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Add sugar to margarine and salt mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook. Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: easy chicken wings
directions: Layer chicken wings in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour Italian dressing over wings.
Sprinkle seasoned bread crumbs on wings.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 60 minutes until done.

title: beef and cheese log
directions: Let cream cheese stand to get soft.
Mix together all ingredients and roll into a log and then into nuts.

title: easy crescent roll casserole
directions: Open and uncoil rolls and place chicken meat in them and roll up.
Layer in casserole dish and cover with soup and milk.
Bake until rolls are done. Top with your favorite grated cheese. Put back in oven until cheese is melted.
Set oven at temperature on crescent roll can.

title: diet soup
directions: Prepare the vegetables by cleaning and cutting them up into medium size pieces and putting them in a large pot of water. Cover with water and let it come to a full boil.
(A small container of onion soup mix may be added at this point for additional flavor, if desired.)
After the soup has boiled about 10 minutes, lower the fire and let it simmer until the vegetables are soft.

title: round eye bread dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, Beau Monde seasoning, dill weed, onion flakes and parsley in a bowl; mix well.
Chill.
Serve in a bread bowl.
Make bowl out of either Hawaiian or rye loaf bread.
Scoop out center, leaving shell.
Cut top and center into cubes for dipping.
May serve with fresh vegetable dippers.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add cooked noodles to ground beef mixture.
Add soup, sauce and water; stir well.
Heat until warm.

title: chili beans
directions: Put ground chuck, onion and green pepper in two cups of water. Cook and stir
until
dry.
Put in tomato juice, chili mix, mushrooms, beans
and cut-up tomatoes.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: rex's green eggs
directions: Drain liquid from greens into pan.
Cook liquid until only a little is left in pan.
Add greens, salt, pepper and margarine and bring to boiling.
Break eggs on top of greens and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook slowly until eggs are done and cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugars, eggs, peanut butter, vanilla and corn syrup.
Beat well.
Add oats, soda and salt.
Beat well. Stir in remainder of ingredients.
Batter will be thick.
Roll and drop 4-inches apart on greased cookie sheet, lightly pressed into Monster Cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cook until center of cookie is soft.
Let cool slightly on cookie sheet, remove and cool completely on a rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: "fudge" cream cheese pie
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell. Chill and serve.

title: "corn" bread
directions: You can use almond flour but hazelnut flour gives more of a corn taste.

title: shortcake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 2 (9-inch) cakes or 1 long pan.
Can be cut in half to make 1 (9-inch) cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: winnie's pickles
directions: Drain
and
slice
pickles.
Mix
other ingredients and bring to
boil.
Put
pickles in jar and pour syrup over them. Will be ready to eat in 4 days.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together and add the rest of the ingredients.
Place 1/2 mixture in casserole, top with shredded Mozzarella cheese, add remaining mixture and another layer of cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and sliced pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green chile enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine soup and Velveeta on low heat.
Add chiles and pimentos.
Put onion and Longhorn cheese with hamburger.
Soften tortillas and roll up.
Pour soup mixture over the top of enchiladas.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ragu casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown beef and simmer with sauce.
Layer ingredients in the following order: macaroni, meat sauce, sour cream and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.
Freezes well.

title: steak teppanyaki
directions: Marinate beef in salt and pepper.
Heat frying pan.
Add oil, then saute garlic until brown.
Pan-fry the beef cubes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook until vegetables are done.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking pan in order given. Do not mix.
Dump in layers.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
This is most unusual and delicious.
Great for lunch boxes and picnics.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt chunks of sharp cheese in liquid mixture of milk and asparagus liquid.
In casserole, layer asparagus, and egg slices for 2 layers.
Thicken cheese liquid with flour.
Add salt and pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, paprika and toasted nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large baking dish (or casserole dish), butter bottom of dish.
Place chicken breasts (add salt, pepper and garlic) in dish.
