On each chicken breast, top with one slice of Swiss cheese. Pour cream of chicken soup on top of this, then sprinkle the stuffing on top and melt butter and pour on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: maine blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff. Cream 3/4 cup sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg yolks.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder and salt, alternately with milk. Fold in beaten egg whites, also berries.

title: favorite cheese cake
directions: Mix both cheeses together.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add flavoring and butter.
Mix well.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° on middle rack for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave in oven for 1/2 hour. Refrigerate and top with fruit, if desired.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl whisking until coffee granules dissolve and all ingredients are well blended.
Pour liqueur into containers with lids.	Chill at least 3 weeks before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix crushed wafers and melted butter and eggs.
Beat and pour over crust.
Add pineapple and slice bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries.

title: chicken pacifica
directions: Combine sour cream with tarragon, thyme, garlic powder, paprika and salt.
Dip pieces of chicken into sour cream mixture, then into cornflake crumbs, coating well.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Place chicken, skin side down, in dish.
Bake for 45 minutes; turn and bake approximately 20 minutes longer.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Brown beef, onions and green pepper; add salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, spaghetti sauce, pizza sauce, pizza seasoning, celery salt and parsley flakes.
Bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes. Mix spaghetti sauce and pepperoni.
Put 1/2 in a 9 x 13-inch can pan.
Layer Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Put in other half of spaghetti, then another layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts then turn oven on low until ready to serve. Freezes well.
Good warmed up.

title: dirt pie
directions: Crush cookies and put half of the crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth with a mixer.
Fold in powdered sugar and then the whipped topping.
In a separate bowl mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold cream cheese and pudding mixtures together.
Pour into pan with the cookie crumbs. Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
This may be frozen or just chilled.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together. Mix in eggs and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients and set aside.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, 1 large can pineapple, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together.
Pour in crust.
Top with 1 can of pineapple and chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water in saucepan for 20 minutes or until tender.
Chill.
Remove skins and dice potatoes into a large bowl.
Stir in celery, onion, pimento and green pepper.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Stir lightly into vegetables.
Blend salad.
Tastes best when chilled to blend flavors.

title: old-fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Cook and stir onion and celery in margarine in medium skillet ove medium heat until tender.
Stir in seasonings.
Add onion mixture and water or broth to bread cubes in large bowl.
Toss to mix.
Stiff neck and body cavities of turkey.
Roast immediately. Makes 8 cups; enough for a 12 pound turkey.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute seasoning in margarine.
Add milk, soup and crawfish. Simmer 20 minutes. Add cornstarch, if needed for thickening.
Pour in pie shell.
Place other shell on top.
Press edges together. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: tuna cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Roll into a large ball.
Place wax paper around, then Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with any type of crackers.
It is also good on bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts and pick from bone.
Put chicken in greased dish.
Add soups and milk.
Melt butter in chicken broth. Add Stove Top stuffing.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and serve with chips.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell peppers in butter. Add soup, pimentos, Ro-Tel, Velveeta and chicken. Stir to melt cheese. Add pasta to mixture. Cover and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: yankee doodle macaroni
directions: Saute onion, garlic, and mushrooms in hot oil until onions are yellow. Add ground beef and cook until brown. Add tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper; cook slowly, about 45 min. Pour over macaroni. Sprinkle with grated sharp cheddar or parmesan cheese. Serves 6 to 8.

title: monema's candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup or molasses and milk until hardens around pan.
Stir in walnuts; cook and put in pans.

title: quick greek salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Sprinkle liberally with oregano and freshly ground black pepper.
Toss with a dressing of 1 part lemon juice and 2 parts good olive oil.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: On 12-inch round platter, mix 2 cans of refried beans with onion.
Spread over platter.
Spread sour cream over beans. Grate Cheddar cheese, enough to cover sour cream.
Layer tomatoes, then black olives.
Chill overnight.
(Optional: Slice avocado on top of olives.
Brown ground beef and put between refried beans and sour cream.
Top with jalapenos and sliced green onions.)

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Place chocolate morsels, marshmallows and peanut butter in a double boiler.
Over low heat, stir constantly until all ingredients are melted.
Fold pecans into mixture.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Refrigerate 20 to 30 minutes or until set.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: deluxe crabmeat casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter in pan and lightly saut onion, bell pepper, mushrooms and celery.
Then combine all ingredients except herb stuffing and paprika and pour into greased casserole.

title: couch potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until fork tender.
In large skillet, saute cooked chicken and onions in oil until onions are tender.
Add mushrooms and cook until they become softened.
Stir in Manwich sauce, wine, seasonings.
Cut each potato in half and fluff up center with fork.
In each potato, spread 1 teaspoon butter and 1/2 cup of chicken mixture.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix 2 parts of ginger ale to 1 part white grape juice.
Chill until ready to serve.
Beautiful when garnished with frozen pineapple rings.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat olive oil in large, heavy cooking pot.
Crush garlic into the oil. Add bay leaf and onion.
Salt lightly.
Saute over medium heat until onion turns transparent. Add eggplant, wine and tomato juice.
Add herbs. Stir, cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes over low heat.
Add zucchini and peppers.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook until all vegetables are tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix melted margarine, 1/2 cup pecans and flour.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown. Cool.

title: knox blox for the holidays
directions: In large bowl, combine Knox unflavored gelatine and flavored gelatin.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolves.
Pour into pan and cool in refrigerator.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook together all ingredients, except strawberries, until thick. Let cool. Mix with strawberries and pour into baked deep dish pie shell. Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours. Serve with cool whip topping.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Clean and prick potatoes several times; rub shortening over potatoes and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Cut potato in half lengthwise.
Scoop out inside, leaving a thin coating of potato.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: Marinate chicken 24 hours before grilling.
May want to add cherry tomatoes, onions, green peppers and mushrooms to marinade.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk; crush with hands until well mixed.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins; stir well.
Pour oleo in bottom of thick pan.
Add pudding mixture.
Bake until very firm.
Cool and cut into squares.
Serve with sauce.

title: golden mushroom steak
directions: Coat steak in flour and brown in shortening about 10 minutes on each side. Combine soup and water.
Pour over steak. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 1 hour or until tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: confetti dip
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Fold in pickles, pimento and egg.
Cover and chill to blend flavors. Serve as a dip for potato chips, pretzels or raw vegetables. Makes 2 cups.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Stir and let sit overnight in refrigerator to develop the flavor.

title: canned stewed tomatoes
directions: Measure all vegetables after chopping.
Mix all ingredients and pack into clean canning jars within 1/2 inch of top.
Process in hot water bath for 55 minutes.

title: kentucky slaw
directions: Mix shredded cabbage, chopped mango, green onions (diced or cut into small slices), dash of salt and pepper and diced cheese. Add mayonnaise as desired.
You may substitute 1 package of cole slaw mix instead of cabbage.
Cover until ready to serve.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together.
Grease 2 quart casserole with margarine.
Bake at 325° covered for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Mix topping first and let stand (first 4 ingredients).
Have ready the flour, sugar, oleo, egg, soda, salt and vanilla. Combine and cream sugar, oleo and egg; add dry ingredients with sour cream and rhubarb.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Put topping evenly over cake before placing in oven.
Delicious!

title: granny's dumplins
directions: Mix flour and Crisco together.
Add eggs and chicken broth; mix well "with hands" until smooth.
Roll out on floured counter or cloth.
Roll out thin.
Cut into 1 inch pieces. Drop into hot chicken broth.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in shortening.
Add soup, milk and Cheez Whiz; stir until melted.
Add broccoli and rice.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ginger-cream cheese ball
directions: Chop dates, nuts and ginger in food processor or by hand. Blend into cheese.
Chill 2 hours and form into 1 large ball or 2 small ones.
Cover with coconut.
Serve with gingersnaps.
Makes 20 servings.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add all but pecans and crust.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into frozen pie crust.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven on a preheated baking sheet for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed sea shells
directions: Cook shells as directed on package.
Cook spinach and drain well. Add cheeses and salt. Mix well. Fill shells with spinach mixture. Add ground beef to spaghetti sauce and pour over shells. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade instant cocoa
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Mix 1/3 cup hot chocolate per cup of boiling water.
This keeps for a long time.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Heat broccoli, celery and onion in saucepan for 10 minutes. Cook rice as directed on box.
Put Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup together and stir until smooth.
Add milk.
Put broccoli, celery and onion in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Pour rice and Cheez Whiz mixture over broccoli.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini chicken
directions: Cut chicken into medium size pieces, brown in the 2 tablespoons of oil, browning on all sides.
Add onions and bell pepper to the chicken and saute until onion is soft.
Add squash, tomatoes, corn and all spices.

title: mrs. lauritsen's danish pudding
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Combine egg nog, sugar and cornstarch in a heavy pan.
Heat until it steams.
Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring to blend.
Stir in rum. Refrigerate until the pudding begins to set.
Fold in whipped cream and turn into a decorative serving bowl.
Refrigerate until served.
Spoon preserved lingon berries over the pudding or serve with a favorite fruit sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine lukewarm water, sugar and yeast; set aside.
In separate bowl mix together remaining ingredients.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Place in greased bowl.
Lightly oil top of dough.
Will keep in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.
Punch down dough and form into balls.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 27 rolls.

title: town house chicken casserole
directions: Spray dish with Pam.
Place chicken in bottom of dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken. Crush crackers. Sprinkle over mixture.
Melt butter and drizzle over crackers. Top with poppy seed. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until casserole bubbles.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Dip in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vbs sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar. Add egg and mix well. Add salt, vanilla and flour. Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into fancy shapes. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until slightly golden. Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until lightly browned.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Blend other ingredients except cheese and bacon.
Pour over onions.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese before baking, or bacon after baking.
Excellent without toppings.

title: ken's deer chili
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and save.
Cook chopped onion and garlic until onion is transparent.
Add ground beef and deer meat.
Cook until it turns from pink to gray.
Add seasonings.
Cook for 5 minutes more.
Add the tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook covered for 45 minutes more, then add the honey, Tabasco, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook for at least 1 hour.
Serve with corn tostados or corn tortillas, chopped onions, grated cheese and jalapeno slices.

title: cheese garlic biscuits(similar to those served at red lobster)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a medium bowl, combine Bisquick, milk and cheese with a spoon until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: gork and gobble
directions: Mix in huge bowl.

title: raisin puff cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft; drain and cool.
Mix together and cream the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients well and add to the creamed margarine mixture.
Add 1/2 cup nuts if desired.
Gently fold in the drained raisins.
Roll into balls; roll dough balls in sugar.
Place dough balls on ungreased baking sheets and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
These are like a soft Snickerdoodle only with raisins.

title: biscuit supreme
directions: Mix together with your hands (it helps to flour your hands first).
Press dough out with your hands on a floured surface. Cut with glass to desired size biscuits you want.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with stew or cover with honey or syrup.

title: dilly dips
directions: Mix together.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: beef 'n biscuit casserole
directions: In frying pan, brown beef and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough. Separate dough into 10 biscuits, pulling each into 2 layers. Press 10 layers into bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine 1/2 Cheddar cheese with sour cream and egg.
Mix well.
Add to meat mixture.
Pour over dough in square pan.
Place remaining layers of dough on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and add sugar gradually; add eggs, one at a time; add flour gradually.
Combine milk and flavors with mixture and pour into cake pan.
Place in a cold oven and cook at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: overnight biuivch casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with cheese.
Crumble bacon over cheese. Sprinkle chilies over bacon.
Beat eggs, add milk, mustard, soup and broth; mix well.
Pour this over bread, cheese and bacon mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Sift together flour, ginger, cloves, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg. Beat egg; add butter and molasses with egg, then alternate flour and milk mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix together all ingredients well. Shape into balls and let rise 1 hour or more.
Bake until golden brown.

title: sausage rotel dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Cube cheese.
Take core out of tomatoes.
Mix all together, cover and microwave.

title: black walnut fudge
directions: Place milk, sugar and butter in saucepan.
Let cook to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Cool and beat until creamy. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Put in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg. Blend in sifted dry ingredients and mashed bananas.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate chex treats
directions: Measure cereal into large bowl; set aside.
Heat chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter in 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until melted.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal in bowl, stirring until evenly coated.
Pour into large bag; add powdered sugar.
Seal and shake until well coated. Spread onto waxed paper to cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chili(hot)
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add chili seasonings and other spices. In large saucepan, combine all other ingredients and let simmer for 15 minutes on medium heat until piping hot.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful in hot vegetable oil until brown.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing. Shape as desired. Roll in paprika, then in bacon bits. Cover with wrap and refrigerate until solid. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: crab pilau
directions: Clean crab meat by removing shells.
Place in mixing bowl. Add lime juice, salt and pepper.
Saute chopped clove of garlic, spring/green onion, minced onions and chopped bell pepper in cooking oil.
Add tomato puree or soup and whole hot green pepper; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add butter and 1/2 cup of coconut milk; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add remaining coconut milk and crab meat. Bring to a boil.
Add washed rice.
Cover tightly.
Reduce heat and steam until rice is cooked.

title: tommy toe tomatoes
directions: Ingredient amounts will vary according to the number of Tommy Toes desired.

title: quiche
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Thaw spinach and squeeze out moisture. Beat eggs, and add other ingredients.
Put in greased pie plate. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes its own crust.

title: garlic bread to die for
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let cream cheese and butter soften at room temperature.
Blend together butter and cream cheese; add garlic and stir in cheese.
Cut loaf of French bread in half; lengthwise.
Spread cheese and butter mixture on both halves of bread.
Place on cookie sheet face up.
Heat in oven for about 10 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook the carrots in salt water (not done).
Drain off and cool in ice water.
While cooking the carrots, prepare the vegetables. Set aside.
After carrots are cooled, mix all together in a bowl. Set aside.
Put the remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Refrigerate for 12 hours or overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut the sliced tenderloin into strips 1/4-inch wide. Brown quickly in butter or margarine in skillet. Push meat to one side. Add mushrooms and onions. Cook until tender, but not brown. Add condensed beef broth. Heat just to boiling. Blend sour cream with flour. Stir into broth. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened (sauce will be thin). Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve over hot rice or buttered noodles. Serves 5 to 6.

title: indian corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crushed pineapple drop cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and pineapple alternately; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Mix butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolk, then other ingredients, except egg white and reserved nuts.
Pat into greased cookie pan.
Beat egg white slightly and brush on top.
Lightly sprinkle with remainder of nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Drain green beans and put over ground beef layer. Pour mushroom soup over the green beans.
Lay Tater Tots over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: macadamia nut-white chocolate pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 14 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter swirl brownies
directions: Reserve 1 tablespoon butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Microwave chocolate and remaining butter.
Stir together remaining sugar, eggs and vanilla, then stir in flour.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix reserved butter and sugar into peanut butter. Spoon over brownie mixture and swirl with a knife to marbleize. Bake at 350` for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: light as a cloud biscuits
directions: Blend all ingredients together quickly with mixer. Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Reheats very well.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift together the flour, salt and soda. Stir into creamed mixture. Stir in oats, dates and nuts. Form into small balls.
Place about 1 1/2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool slightly before removing to cooling rack.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: warren's rabbit stew
directions: Cut up rabbit and soak in salt water for about 1/2 hour. Drain off water and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper; dredge in flour.
Heat shortening in frying pan and brown rabbit well. Add 1 cup water. Cover and simmer about 1 hour or until tender. Make a thickener using 1 tablespoon flour in 1/2 cup water and stir until smooth.
Pour around rabbit.
Stir until thickened. Cook a little longer and serve with hot biscuits.

title: all-american chili
directions: Saute the onions, green peppers and garlic in butter.
Put in large pot.
Brown the meat; drain.
Put everything in the pot. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican hamburger casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish starting with tortillas and ending with as much cheese as desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, water and puree; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Place bread cubes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour melted margarine over bread cubes; add hot tomato mixture.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Good served with poultry.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Melt butter on a cookie sheet in a 350° oven.
Put pecans in to heat for 5 minutes.
Mix well.
Put in oven for 5 minutes.
Mix Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce together.
Pour over pecans and mix well.
Salt well.
Put in oven for 5 minutes.
Mix.
Put in oven for 5 minutes.
Check and take out if good.

title: cranberry-apple-pear sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients except liqueur in large pan to boiling, stirring frequently, to prevent burning.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently until mixture thickens, about 45 minutes.
Take off heat; stir in Cointreau.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 4 hours.
Better overnight or longer.
Serve chilled with turkey.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Make rice and broccoli according to directions.
Drain; set aside.
In casserole dish, mix soup, cheese and butter.
Stir in broccoli and rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: hot fudge sauce 1
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and milk and salt.
Heat and boil a few minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.

title: jan's easy pot roast
directions: Rub frozen roast with salt and pepper.
Pour A.1. sauce over covering well.
Place on large sheet of heavy-duty foil and pull up ends to make tight folds.
Place in open roasting pan, and pour in a little water to keep foil from sticking.
Roast in a 325° oven for 5 hours.
Open foil carefully and remove roast to plate.
Pour out drippings, thicken with flour and water paste and boil a few minutes to make gravy.
Quartered onions may be cooked with roast for extra flavor.

title: baked stuffed cabbage
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Line it with cabbage.
Saute onion and meat until browned.
Pour off grease.
Make one layer of hamburger-onion mixture over cabbage and 1/2 can tomato soup. Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian macaroni salad
directions: Separate fruit from the juice; save broth. While cooking the macaroni, prepare the fruit sauce. Mix sugar, flour, salt, eggs and the fruit juices in a saucepan. Once the sauce comes to a boil, remove from heat. The sauce will thicken as it cools. Mix the sauce and cooked macaroni and allow it to cool in the refrigerator for about 4 hours or overnight. Then fold in whipped topping, marshmallows and fruit. Chill until ready to serve. Makes about 6 quarts.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook and peel potatoes (boil).
Brown onion in 1 tablespoon of bacon fat.
After onion is browned, add everything in but potatoes and kielbasa.
Put these in separate large bowl.
Pour mixture over top.
Serve warm.
Reheat in microwave or oven.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain all the beans.
Add chopped onion.
Add the bottle of salad dressing and mix well. This is a good recipe for anyone watching their sugar intake.

title: tex-mex cornbread salad
directions: Crumble half of the cornbread into the bottom of a large serving bowl.
Top with half of the beans.
In another bowl, combine tomatoes, onions, green pepper and jalapeno peppers. Blend well.
Spread half of the mixture over the beans.
Sprinkle with half of the bacon and half of the cheese.
Stir together sour cream and salsa.
Spread half of the dressing over the cheese. Repeat layers.
Garnish with sour cream and jalapeno pepper slices, if desired.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Place crab meat in mixing bowl.
Sprinkle crumbs over crab lightly.
In another bowl mix egg, mayonnaise, salt, mustard, parsley, cayenne, Tabasco and white pepper.
Mix together and add to crab meat mixture.
Shape into small cakes.
Fry in hot Crisco oil at 350° until brown on both sides, turning once.
Makes about 50 small cakes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Flatten with meat mallet.
Roll up as for jelly rolls.
Wrap with bacon; secure with toothpicks. Sprinkle dried beef in crock-pot.
Arrange chicken rolls over beef. Top with mixture of soup and sour cream.
Cook on low for 12 hours. Yield:
8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in very small amount of water. Drain and mash. Mix with sour cream and soup. Add onion and carrot. Grease dish. Put squash mixture in dish. Cover with dressing mix and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan combine potatoes, water, onion and chicken bouillon granules.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook over medium-high heat about 20 minutes until potatoes are tender. Transfer to blender; cover and blend until smooth.
Remove mixture and add enough skim milk to make 5 cups.
Return mixture to saucepan.
In small saucepan melt margarine.
Stir in parsley, pimento, flour, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Stir into potato mixture.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese; cook and stir until cheese melts.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and add dry ingredients.
Add oats, nuts and coconut.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Drain water from canned artichokes and oil from marinated artichokes; reserve oil.
Place artichokes into blender.
Puree with some of the oil.
Add bread crumbs and cheese and mix. Mixture must be shaped into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Add tuna, soup and milk to cooked noodles.
Mix well.
Bake in greased lasagna pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle crushed potato chips over top and bake for an additional 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned corn bread
directions: Put bacon grease into pan or cast iron skillet, melt in 425° oven.
Tilt melted grease to cover bottom and sides.
Mix together the corn meal, flour and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and melted butter. Stir just until moist.
Pour batter into greased pan or skillet. Bake until golden brown.

title: cornbread taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Brown ground beef and pepper. Drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, and tomato sauce. Pour in 2 qt. casserole dish.
In small bowl prepare corn meal mix according to package.
Stir in half can of onions.
Spoon in batter around meat mixture.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.
Top corn bread with remaining onions and cheese.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes longer until onions are brown.

title: foundation fruit punch
directions: Mix sugar and water and bring to boil.
Then let cool.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Ginger ale may be substituted for part or all of water.
Add just before serving.

title: jane's asparagus casserole
directions: Place one can of asparagus in baking dish.
Slice 2 hard-boiled eggs over asparagus.
Spread one can of mushroom soup over these ingredients.
Mix together the grated Cheddar and Mozzarella and place 1/2 of cheese mixture over all.
Layer in same order the remaining ingredients, except Durkee onions.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until bubbly.
The last 5 minutes sprinkle onions on top.
This recipe makes a large casserole.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: *If you don't have savory, you can substitute with 1/8 teaspoon sage.

title: tuna and biscuit
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Can use canned or make own biscuit dough.
If canned dough is used, break each into halves or thirds. Roll each piece of dough very thin. Place about a teaspoon of the tuna
mix on each rolled out strip of dough, and roll and close in a log shape, leaving both ends open.
Place, seam side down, and bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes. Makes about 20.

title: cheesy meatballs in spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese cubes.
Form into meatballs.
Push a cube of cheese into each meatball.
Brown meatballs in hot oil.
Make sauce.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring the ingredients to a boil.
Lower heat and cook slowly for 3/4 of an hour and stir occasionally.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and shortening; put aside 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Add molasses and baking soda-water mixture. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; pour crumbs on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Fry onions in oil until tender; add flour and stock; cook until thick.
Add tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; simmer ten minutes.
In another pan, brown beef and mushrooms; drain.
Add beef to sauce.
Just before serving, add sour cream; serve on rice or noodles.

title: n.t.l. chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, brown meats. Add garlic and sprinkle with celery salt, onion salt, lemon pepper and ground cumin.
Drain off most of fat.
Add diced celery, onion and green peppers and beer.
Continue to cook over low heat until onion is white and tender.
Sprinkle generously again with celery salt, onion powder, lemon pepper and coarse ground pepper.
Add 2 tablespoons ground cumin and Worcestershire sauce.
Continue cooking over low heat (10 minutes).
Add canned tomatoes.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 2 cups bran and set aside.
Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, beat well.
Mix in buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Add bran mixture and 1 cup dry bran.
Add options.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well.
Place dip in hollowed out loaf of brown bread. Bread chunks may be used as dippers as well as vegetables.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Add parsley and pepper to season.

title: party salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and sweetened condensed milk in a large bowl and refrigerate one hour.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir well and refrigerate overnight.
Do not attempt to mold.

title: chicken in a hurry
directions: On stove top, put in first 4 ingredients.
Boil.
Add rice and turn down.
Let rice soak up all the juice.
Can garnish with chives, French fried onions or cheese.

title: christmas ham
directions: About 6 1/2 hours before serving or early in day:

Remove skin and trim excess fat from pork leg, leaving only a thin fat covering. Place pork, fat side up, on rack in large roasting pan. With hands, rub cracked pepper and 2 teaspoons salt over pork. Cover roast loosely with a tent of foil. Insert meat thermometer into center of thickest part of pork, being careful that pointed end of thermometer does not touch bone. Roast pork in 325° oven about 6 hours or until meat thermometer reaches 160° to 170° (about 23 to 25 minutes per pound). Pork near bone will be pink. After pork has roasted 4 hours, remove foil. After pork has roasted 5 hours, sprinkle roast with chopped parsley. When pork is done, place on platter; let stand 15 minutes for easier carving.

title: finger pie(old fashioned sugar cream pie)
directions: Dot with butter before baking.
Stir in an unbaked pie crust with fingers.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then reduce heat to 350° and bake until shakes in pan like jelly.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Boil sliced zucchini for 10 minutes.
Melt margarine, soup and sour cream.
Add seasoning, zucchini and stuffing cubes.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber "apple rings"
directions: Peel, slice and seed cucumbers.
Soak in the lime and 1 gallon of water for 24 hours; drain and rinse.
Soak in ice water 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: no cholesterol egg substitute(equals 2 whole eggs)
directions: Blend ingredients together and use in recipes calling for whole eggs.
This is delicious alternative for those on cholesterol restricted diets.
It contains no cholesterol, reduced fat and calories and more protein than 2 whole eggs.

title: wilted leaf lettuce salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble, reserving drippings.
Add onion to drippings; cook until tender.
Add vinegar, 1/4 cup water, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and bacon; cook and stir until boiling.
Place lettuce in bowl; pour hot dressing over.
Toss to coat.
Garnish with radishes and egg.

title: potato salad mold
directions: Mix gelatin and sugar thoroughly in saucepan.
Stir in water. Place over low heat; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Blend in evaporated milk, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar and pepper.
Chill until slightly thickened; stir occasionally.
Toss potatoes with Italian salad dressing.
Mix potatoes, eggs, celery, olives and onion powder with thickened gelatin mixture.
Turn into a 5 1/2-cup ring mold.
Chill about 4 hours.
Unmold onto a chilled platter.
Garnish with leaf lettuce and fill center with cherry tomatoes.

title: orange jello refrigerator cake
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water; later add the cold water.
Cool to room temperature.
Bake cake as directed.
Poke holes in warm cake with toothpick.
Slowly pour jello over warm cake.
Refrigerate cake while making topping.

title: cup-a-cobbler]
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Pour into pan.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes.
Crust should surface and become golden brown.

title: carrot (pumpkin or squash) cake
directions: Soften cheese and butter. Blend in remaining ingredients until smooth. Add coconut flakes and nuts to suit taste (1/4 to 1/2 cup each).

title: veggie pizza
directions: Pat rolls flat on two 14-inch pizza pans.
Cook 8 to 9 minutes at 375°.
Combine mayonnaise and cream cheese and spread on cooled crust.
Cut crust.
Also add salt.
Put chopped veggies on top.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine for crust.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on chilled crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix first four ingredients and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven and cool.
Remove 1/3 for topping.
Beat egg whites, sugar, berries and lemon juice at low speed for 2 minutes.
Use large bowl, then beat at high speed until stiff peaks form (about 10 minutes).
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon over crumb mixture. Sprinkle top with reserved crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix the ingredients and shape into balls.
Cover with Prego sauce.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.
Uncover and add grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until melted.

title: no-bake drop cookies
directions: In a large pan, add sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and boil one minute.
Remove from heat, then add crunchy peanut butter.
Stir to dissolve, then add oats and vanilla, then drop on waxed paper and let set.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: fruit sherry pork chops
directions: Trim all but thin layer of fat pork chops.
In heavy skillet, render some of the trimmed fat to coat pan lightly.
Discard excess fat.
Rub flour seasoned with salt and pepper into both sides of chops.
Brown on both sides over medium heat.
Cut 3 (1/4 inch) slices from center of orange.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Combine juices with sherry.
Pour over and around chops.
Cover pan tightly.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Add pineapple rings and juices last 1/2 hour of cooking.
Remove chops and fruit.
Thicken pan juices slightly with little cornstarch mixed with cold water if desired.

title: red cabbage(germany)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vinegar and butter in a large pan.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 1/2 hour or until the cabbage is tender.
Remove from heat.
Add the vinegar and butter and toss lightly.
Serve hot.
Serve with the beef rouloden or the sauerbraten for a super meal.
Don't forget the potato dumplings.

title: ranch stew
directions: Cut carrots and potatoes in pieces.
Put raw meat in and pour other ingredients in a roasting pan.
Bake at 250° for 6 hours (never raise the lid).

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Mushroom Caps:
Blend the filling ingredients with a fork. Remove stems from mushrooms and fill with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (until bubbly and golden brown).

title: mrs. burns pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix flour and pecans.
Spread in small baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Bake at 325° until lightly brown, about 15 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli and sliced chicken; mix all other ingredients and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Then top with grated cheese. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 250°.
Remove foil and add 1/2 cup butter or margarine to 1 package Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing seasoned dressing mix.
Put on top of casserole and return to oven; bake for 1/2 hour.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, garlic, green pepper and celery in bacon drippings or oil until onion is golden.
Add thyme and bay leaves; stir well.
Add Tabasco, Ro-Tel, tomatoes, tomato sauce, 2 cups water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice; reduce heat. Cook, covered 30 minutes.
Add chicken and Polish sausage.
Cook until rice is tender.
Add more Tabasco if needed.

title: elephant ears
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
In large bowl, sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Add milk mixture and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add 4 cups flour until stiff.
Knead.
Fry in 375° oil for 3 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or powdered sugar.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Combine flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the sour milk.
Add bananas and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in loaf pan or 2 layer cake pans at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: cornbread and sage dressing
directions: Combine cornbread, biscuits and chicken broth.
Soak for 30 minutes. Add onion, celery and eggs.
Stir in butter and sage. Bake until celery and onions are done and brown on top.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Mix together and put in a shallow dish. Freeze overnight. Let set at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, sugar, oil, eggs and undrained pineapple (mix only by hand).
Add bananas and nuts; mix again.
Bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool in pan 1 hour before removing from pan.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat well with mixer. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: my favorite stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Cut out of core of cabbage and place in container of boiling water until leaves come loose. (Do not overcook.)
When leaves cool slightly, roll meat in leaves.
With pointing finger, tuck in the ends.
Place in bottom of pan a layer of extra leaves, then cabbage rolls and a layer of sauerkraut. Cover with juice and the crushed tomatoes on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 2 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and fold all together.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cut drained broccoli into 1 inch pieces.
Line square, buttered casserole with broccoli pieces.
Combine undiluted soup with chopped onions, mayonnaise and beaten eggs.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle dry stuffing over all.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: perfect dinner rolls
directions: Mix the first four ingredients and cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1 c. warm water, add 1 egg, add to above.
Beat in 2 1/2 c. flour and then by hand add another 2 to 2 1/2 c. flour.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double.
Grease hands and break into pieces and place in greased oblong pan and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This recipe may also be used for cinnamon rolls, reduce sugar to 1/4 c.

title: baked fish
directions: Coat fish with mayonnaise and place on baking sheet.
Spread the crushed potato chips evenly over the fish, then cover well with the shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy coconut custard
directions: Mix all together and blend well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until crust is brown and custard is firm.

title: creamy peppercorn dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill well before serving. Dressing will keep for about 2 weeks.

title: almond crunch cookies
directions: Cream together until fluffy the butter, sugar and packed brown sugar.
Blend in the eggs and vanilla.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Put breasts in tortillas, folded in half. Mix soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes; pour over tortillas.
Cook for 30 minutes at 325°.
Add cheese; cook for an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, eggs and cocoa together.
Blend in flour and vanilla. Add nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Immediately after taking out of oven, sprinkle miniature marshmallows over top of cake.

title: lemon pilaf
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender and clear.
Toss gently with rice.
Add the lemon peel, the juice of one lemon, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly over low heat or in microwave.
Sprinkle top with almonds and serve.
Good with chicken or seafood.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add other ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: kielbasa and tomato omelette
directions: In medium saucepan, cook fresh tomatoes.
While simmering, add tomato sauce and continue to simmer.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In small frypan, fry kielbasa.
When cooked, add to sauce; set aside.
Scramble eggs.
In a large frypan, cook eggs in omelette shape.
When done, put filling in middle.
Add 1/2 of cheese.
Fold over and put remaining cheese on top.

title: as you like it salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Add remaining ingredients. You may also add green pepper, onion, peanuts, sunflower seeds, etc. Serve with dressing.

title: barb's apple salad
directions: Wash and quarter apples.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Add dates and nuts.
Mix dressing, Cool Whip and salt in a small bowl. Mix all together.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit 'n yogurt pie
directions: Thoroughly combine mashed fruit and yogurt in a bowl.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon mixture into crust and freeze for 4 hours.
Can serve frozen or place in refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.
If frozen solid, may require more than 30 minutes to soften.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: garbanzo bean dip
directions: Place garbanzos, lemon juice, garlic, salt and water in blender or processor.
Puree or blend well.
Add more water if a thinner consistency is desired.
Garnish with fresh parsley and drizzle olive oil over the top.
Serve as an appetizer with chips or pita bread.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk until smooth. Add lemon juice to the taste. Pour into the crust and refrigerate for several hours. Top with cherry pie filling. Serve. Makes 1 pie.

title: rice pot crawfish jambalaya(serves 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients in rice pot.
Cook until done.
Serve. To double recipe:

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with stuffing, which has been tossed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Slice top off bread.
Cut inside bread and top slice.
Mix all ingredients.
Dip and fill bread hollow.
Arrange cubes around bread.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together with mixer or blender.
Add 1 cup coconut and 1 can crushed pineapple, drained.
Chill.
Use to dip fresh fruit.

title: mom's oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Do not peel.
Cut each potato into 6 wedges. Dry potatoes slightly with paper towels so that spices will stick. Mix all the spices and cheese with oil.
Stir well to blend. Pour over potatoes and stir until they are evenly coated.
Spread out onto 2 shallow baking pans.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until tender.
Stir twice during baking and sprinkle with more cheese if desired.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, cornstarch and salt in a bowl.
Add and stir in the butter, egg yolk and grated Parmesan cheese.
Mix all the ingredients to get a dough.
Let it stand for 10 minutes, then roll it to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into shapes with metal cookie cutters.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole (1 large or 2 small).
Bake in a 375° oven until bubbly, 30 to 45 minutes. Easily frozen.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine according to directions and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to noodles and refrigerate.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Store in closed container.

title: king's crabs
directions: Clean crabs.
Boil water, salt, oil, vinegar and 1/2 the Old Bay.
When boiling, add crabs.
Bring to second boil.
Pour in beer and more Old Bay.
Cook 10 minutes.
Let sit for 30 minutes after removed from water.
Then grub!

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mash cream cheese; blend in mayonnaise and salt.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in fruit cocktail and nuts.
Spoon into baking dish and freeze for several hours or overnight.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight. Dip in 12 ounces chocolate chips and 1 large cake paraffin wax.

title: brisket
directions: Marinate meat overnight.
Bake at 300 degrees, 1 hour per pound of meat.
Baste with barbecue sauce in the last 30 minutes.

title: butterhorns
directions: Soften	yeast in 1/4 cup warm water (110°). Combine 3/4 cup milk,
scalded,
cup shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons salt; cool to lukewarm. Add 1 cup sifted all-purpose flour;
add yeast and 3 eggs.
Beat well.

title: strawberry cake
directions: If strawberries are fresh, wash, cap, slice and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Let berries stand for about 2 hours, then drain. If using frozen berries, thaw.
Mix in mixing bowl and add strawberries, jello mixture, salad oil and eggs.
Blend on low speed of mixer, then beat on high speed for 4 minutes.
Bake in two 8-inch round pans.
When cool, frost.

title: muesli(swiss oatmeal)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Mix well. Serve with brown sugar and milk or cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Add dry powdered milk, eggs and water to basic mix.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In top of double boiler, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in cold milk.
Cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes longer.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add to remaining mixture in double boiler and cook for 2 minutes over hot, but not boiling, water stirring constantly.
Cool and add vanilla and coconut (reserve some of the coconut for top of meringue). Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake in a moderate oven at 325° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: beef strips sauterne
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Slice thinly across the grain.
Saute beef slices, onion, mushrooms and garlic in oil in 12-inch skillet until beef is no longer pink.
Remove from heat.
Stir in dry nonfat milk, flour, parsley, salt and pepper.
Gradually add water, Sauterne and crumbled bouillon cube.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Serve over hot, cooked noodles.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: chili chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken.
Rub over chicken breast pieces; marinate 8 hours.
Broil chicken on both sides 15 minutes, periodically brushing with mixture.

title: crab lover's spread
directions: Grind (pulverize) imitation crab in food processor or blender. Combine crabmeat, salad dressing mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and horseradish mustard.
Chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add ground beef and
seasonings;
cook until beef is slightly brown.
Add tomato paste
and
water,
mixing well.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. Cook
noodles.
Spoon 1/3 of the sauce into 13 1/2 x 8 3/4
x
1 3/4-inch
baking dish.
Begin to make layers with cheeses, sauce and noodles.
Repeat, ending with Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: professor's squash
directions: Cut zucchini into 1-inch pieces; cook in water until soft. Add grated onion and 1/2 pint of sour cream (8 ounces).
Add remaining croutons on top and bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: golden glow bread
directions: Sift
together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs with milk and fat.
Add
to
dry ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Add the orange
juice,
rind
and corn flakes.
Pour into greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 375° about one hour.

title: leona fuel's date nut cake
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped dates and baking soda; let cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts and dates.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured baking pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Boil raisins for 20 minutes in 2 cups water.
Remove from stove and add Crisco and 1 cup cold water.
Set aside.

title: vonie's swedish cookies
directions: Soften yeast in small amount of cream.	Cut butter into flour with pie
cutter.
Add
yeast to remaining cream and add to flour mixture.
Let
stand
for
hour.
Roll
out
about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut
and
dip
in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Bake until golden brown at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barbecue steak rolls
directions: Sprinkle one side of each cube steak with salt and peper; brush with melted butter, then add Heinz barbecue sauce with onions.
Roll steaks jelly-roll fashion; secure with toothpicks. Brush with barbecue sauce and grill over hot coals, turning occasionally.
Grill for 15 minutes or until desire doneness.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Combine non-instant pudding and milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; add cake mix to pudding.
Beat on medium for 2 minutes.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chips over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Mix soup, tomatoes and seasonings.
Layer ingredients. Top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Can be frozen.

title: citrus tea
directions: *Can substitute with equivalent of lo-cal sweetener.

title: shredded lettuce salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, spread lettuce.
Sprinkle vegetables over lettuce.
Ice with mayonnaise.
Top with cheese, pressing down to thoroughly cover.
Wrap tightly; refrigerate overnight before using.
Will keep 3 to 4 days.
Serves 12 or more.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in long dish (9 x 5 x 2-inch). Mix mayonnaise and sugar; spread over vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon on top.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Scald milk and let cool to lukewarm. Beat sugar, salt and 3 cups of flour into yeast and milk.
Add egg and oil, then the other flour.
Work this together well and let rise in large bowl for 1 1/2 hours or until it doubles.
Work up again and make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
These are delicious spread with butter.

title: beer muffins
directions: With a fork, combine the biscuit mix, oil and beer, stirring until mix is moistened.
Using a level tablespoon, spoon into greased muffin pan cups.
Press a cheese cube into the center of each so the cheese shows.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake on a rack below oven center at 450° about 8 minutes, or until a cake tester inserted off center comes out clean.
Serve at once to preserve the malt flavor.

title: peanut butter corn flake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring while heating.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until mixture is smooth.
Add corn flakes to the syrup mixture, stirring until coated with syrup.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and press down into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: coconut lovers macaroons
directions: Using an electric mixer, beat egg whites and salt on high speed until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in extract and coconut.
Using nonstick baking pan or one sprayed with cooking spray, drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.
Calories: 53.
Fat:
1 gram.
Time involved is 45 minutes.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook boneless breasts and dice.
Mix all ingredients and put into buttered 2 to 2 1/2 quart casserole.
(Do not precook rice.) Spread topping on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: strips of beef casserole
directions: Cut steak into strips; brown in shortening in skillet.
Add onions; cook until lightly brown.
Stir in flour, 1 cup water and remaining ingredients except mushrooms and sour cream.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add mushrooms and sour cream; simmer for 5 minutes longer.
Spoon beef mixture into casserole.

title: frozen cherry loaf
directions: Drain fruits.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in sour cream, sugar and salt.
Fold in fruits, marshmallows and pecans. Pour into large cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Freeze at least 6 hours. Take out approximately 20 to 25 minutes before serving.
Serves 10, but could serve many more for potluck.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Sprinkle 18 x 24 inch piece of heavy duty aluminum foil with powdered sugar. Mix first 3 ingredients in large heavy saucepan and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Boil without stirring until temperature reaches 310 degrees F (drops of syrup make hard brittle threads in cold water). Remove from heat and stir in flavoring oil and coloring. (Be careful when adding these, heat may cause it to splatter.) Pour onto foil quickly to cool. Once completely cooled, break into small pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix potatoes, water and oil together.
Mix all ingredients together and combine with the potato mixture.
Enough batter to bake one in a tube pan and one in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: calico hot dish
directions: Fry bacon.
Add meat and onions; brown.
Mix together with the ingredients in the large bowl.
Place mixture in a large casserole (or 2 small ones).
Bake uncovered for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 9 X 13-inch cake pan with diced rhubarb.
Mix sugar and dry gelatin together.
Sprinkle evenly over rhubarb. Pour dry cake mix over rhubarb mixture, then pour water over all. Melt butter and pour over top.
(Do not mix.)
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: southern fried corn
directions: Shuck corn.
Wash and remove silk.
Cut kernels off corn after cutting the kernels in half with a sharp knife.
Scrape juice out of corncob into the corn.
Add flour, sugar and salt to taste. Stir, then add water.
Fry strips of fatback until all grease is out of meat.
Place fatback aside.
Then add fatback drippings to corn.
Cook over slow heat, stir constantly.
Simmer until corn is tender, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add to Bisquick, then add cheese/salsa. Make balls and bake until brown at 375°.
Place in crock-pot to keep warm.

title: ruby apple salad
directions: Mix gelatin, candies and water.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in apples, celery and walnuts.
Pour in a 1-quart bowl.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Chop onion and bell pepper and steam in small pan.
Boil chicken and save broth.
Mix all soups and Ro-Tel in crock-pot. Let heat and cook together all soups, Ro-Tel, onion and bell pepper.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Debone chicken.
Mix all ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: cocoa rolls
directions: Mix cocoa and powdered sugar well.
Add sweetened milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add pecans and mix together by hand.
Dust your hands in 2 tablespoons cocoa and 2 tablespoons powdered sugar to keep mixture from sticking to hands.
Roll the mixture into balls and roll balls in bowl of 2 tablespoons cocoa and 2 tablespoons powdered sugar.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Fry until browned in shortening.

title: homemade lye soap
directions: Dissolve lye in cold water in iron kettle or granite dish pan. Stir with wooden spoon until lye is dissolved.
Do not breathe the fumes from lye water.
When lye water gets cold, pour grease in and stir till it is mixed well.
Sit in cool place until it gets hard.
Then cut and lay on clean wood or cardboard to dry out.
Always make during the old moon.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: In a large bowl, combine spices and stir in applesauce and glue.
Work mixture 2 or 3 minutes to form a ball.
If too dry, add more applesauce; if too wet, add more cinnamon.

Knead on a cinnamon sprinkled surface until it holds together well. Divide into small portions and roll out until about 1/4-inch thick on cinnamon sprinkled surface and then cut with cookie cutters into desired shapes.
Place on trays or cookie sheets.
Use a pencil to make a small hole in top for hanging ribbon.
Be sure hole goes the whole way through. Air dry the ornaments, turning from time to time, or dry in a 250° to 300° oven for several hours.
Air drying will take several days, depending on humidity and weather.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Boil 2 cups of water with 2 bouillon cubes.
Add carrots, boil until water almost boils out (covered).
Add 1 cup water and 1 bouillon cube and 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Continue boiling until carrots are tender.
Remove from heat and let stand covered 15 minutes then add remaining brown sugar.
Stir, simmer until thick. Serve hot.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in glass bowl.
Cook on High for 8 minutes, stirring once after 4 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla; mix well.
Cook on High another 2 minutes.
Remove bowl from microwave.
Add the baking soda.
Stir quickly; pour onto cookie sheet or aluminum pie pan sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Let cool.
Pop out of pan; break into pieces.

title: hacienda hamburger
directions: Cut olives into small pieces.
Heat oil, add meat and cook about 5 minutes stirring frequently.
Stir in onions and celery and cook about 5 minutes longer.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes, olives, uncooked noodles and cheese.
Cover tightly and cook until mixture is boiling.
Remove cover and stir lightly but thoroughly. Cover and cook slowly on low heat about 20 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat butter or margarine with electric mixer on medium speed until softened.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
With mixer on low speed, add flour and potato chips, beating until well mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoons about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten dough with a fork that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken pot pie 2
directions: In a large oblong pan layer in order:
chicken, vegetables and sliced eggs.
In saucepan, heat together broth, margarine and soup. Pour mixture over layers.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix well and pour evenly over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: "mary's beans"
directions: Fry bacon brown in wok or large skillet.
Crumble crisp bacon up	in small pieces.
Chop onions, pepper, mushrooms and chestnuts up	and
stir-fry
in
the	bacon
grease
for a few minutes. Drain
beans
and add to stir-fry.	Add bacon pieces and seasonings as desired.
Stir-fry until hot.
Very good.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef on top of range in skillet.
Saute onion and green peppers together.
Mix hamburger, sauteed onion and peppers, mushroom soup and uncooked rice together in casserole dish. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Mix in celery, peppers and onions. Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.
Cook in electric skillet.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: lemon ginger vinaigrette
directions: Place all ingredients into blender and pour in warm water until mixture thickens.

title: corn relish
directions: Chop vegetables the desired size and cook each separately. Cook until tender, not soft.
Drain cooked vegetables and mix together.
Combine sugar, salt, mustard, water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and add to vegetable mixture.
Put in jars and cook in pressure cooker for 30 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: new year's good luck salad
directions: Make Layer 3 first.

title: stephanie's company jello
directions: Make blue jello according to package directions.
Refrigerate and let set approximately 1 hour.
Mix in fruit.
Refrigerate until set.
Sprinkle on decoration sprinkles.
Serve.
Kids love it and love the color!

title: peppered steak
directions: Brown meat slowly in hot fat (about 15 minutes).
Add onion and garlic last few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water and add to meat.
Cover and simmer until meat is almost tender (25 minutes or so).
Add tomato and green pepper.

title: garlic gnocchi
directions: Boil potatoes and mash.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Form into ball.
Divide in 1/2.
Break off golf ball size pieces.
Roll out on floured surface with palms of hands to long string 3/4-inch thick.
Cut 1-inch size pieces.
Cook in large pot of boiling water, until they come to surface.
Use slotted spoon, drain.
Work in small batches.
After all are cooked, cover with spaghetti sauce and serve.

title: quick caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Place popped corn in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Combine butter and brown sugar in a 2 cup glass measuring cup.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Mixture must boil at least 1 minute.
Stir once or twice.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Pour syrup mixture over popped corn.

title: party rye rounds
directions: Mix well.
Spread over 2 loaves party rye bread.
Put on cookie sheets, then under broiler.
Watch as they burn fast.
I use canned cheese.

title: ginger cookies(old-time recipe)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add molasses and eggs; beat well.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls and roll in sugar; press (not thin).
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.
This recipe is over 80 years old.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, then syrup.
Add flour. Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake in long pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until tests done.

title: meatball surprise (microwave)
directions: Drain olives.
Mix taco mix with ground beef.
Surround each olive with 1 tablespoon meat.
Place meatballs in circular fashion on paper plate.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Can be frozen ahead.

title: pima indian bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening as for biscuits.
Add enough water to make a dough easy to handle. Work dough to a very smooth texture.
This is important and means you must knead the dough until it is soft, yet elastic.

title: chow-chow
directions: Combine vegetables and mix with salt.
Cover; let stand overnight and drain.
Mix mustard with a little vinegar in kettle. Add remaining vinegar, sugar and spices.
Simmer 20 minutes. Add vegetables and simmer 10 minutes.
Continue simmering while packing one hot sterilized jar at a time.
Fill to within 1/8-inch from jar top.
Make sure liquid covers vegetables.
Seal each jar at once.
Process in boiling water bath (212°F) for 5 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 pints.
Use relish within 6 months.

title: hamburger-potato casserole
directions: Brown the hamburg with the onion and pepper.
Drain.
Place hamburg in bottom of casserole. Top with mushrooms and layer with sliced potatoes and onion to top of casserole.
Place diluted mushroom soup over the casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May top with shredded Cheddar cheese before serving.

title: mapley pecan pie
directions: Add syrup to eggs; stir in sugar, salt and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Combine with chicken, pineapple, celery and almonds.
Toss lightly and chill.

title: strawberry cheese spread
directions: In a saucepan, combine berries, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook, uncovered, over moderate heat, stirring and mashing berries for 45 minutes or until mixture is very thick and most of the liquid has evaporated.
Cool.
In a bowl, cream together the cream cheese, butter and salt.
Add berry mixture.
Serve as a breakfast spread.

title: marie's cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Pour out on two baking sheets (greased) until 1/4 or 1/3 inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cut on bias to make diamonds.
While warm, drizzle confectioners sugar mixed with cream and vanilla over cookies while still warm.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Blend oleo, oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients with milk.
Blend well; add zucchini.
Pour in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inches or Bundt pan).
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, until done.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Spoon mixture over 4 chicken breasts and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: zucchini pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs fluffy; add sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini and mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in rest.
Bake in two greased loaf pans for one hour at 320° or two 8 x 2-inch square pans.
I use a 13 x 9-inch pan, but time may not be the same.
Cool and frost.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix chicken, cheese and soup together.
Pour over broccoli in medium baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together dry ingredients. Pour in applesauce. Combine orange juice and egg; add to dry ingredients, mixing just enough to moisten. Add in cranberries and nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan for at least an hour. Check for doneness.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave 15 to 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: *I prefer regular oats, but instant will do.

title: minestrone
directions: Saute onion, garlic, carrots and celery in oil until brown. Add water; simmer 15 minutes.
Add everything else, except spaghetti.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add spaghetti and cook 10 minutes. Serve hot.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: shake pickles
directions: Slice cukes in gallon jug to the rim.
Mix brine well, do not cook; pour over cukes and shake.
Keep on counter for 5 days and shake every day 2 or 3 times a day.
After 5 days, refrigerate. Will keep for months.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and rice.
Saute 10 minutes or until mixture is a pale yellow.
Add consomme, water and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole and cover.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed.
Serve garnished with almonds.

title: chicken company style
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Remove excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken. Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.
Can be served over rice.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over batter.
Drain pineapple (use syrup as part of liquid in cake).
Arrange pineapple and maraschino cherry halves on the sugar mixture.
Mix cake mix according to directions on the package.
Pour batter over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes (until cake pulls away from side of pan).
Let stand 5 minutes. Turn upside down onto large platter.

title: seafood pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Saute 1 tablespoon oil, garlic, shrimp and scallops until almost done.
Do not overcook!
Drain off juice. Spread 1/2 tablespoon oil over pie crust.
Add shrimp, scallops and garlic and spread over pie crust evenly.
Spread seafood flakes evenly.
Add 1/2 of both shredded cheeses.
Spread asparagus evenly and add rest of shredded cheeses.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan over top and bake until crust and cheese get slightly brown, 8 to 10 minutes approximately.

title: dog bones
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Knead dough 2 minutes. On a floured surface, use a floured rolling pin to roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Use a bone-shaped cookie cutter to cut out bones.
(Any shape will do.)
Bake 30 minutes on an ungreased baking sheet.
Remove from pan and cool.
Dogs love their dog bones!

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Form meat balls; fry in butter.
Serve in pretty casserole dish.

title: banana bread
directions: In a bowl, mix together bananas and well-beaten eggs; add oil. Stir together, then add flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Bake in a greased 9 x 5-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or until pick comes clean.
Remove from pan to cool.
(I put waxed paper in bottom of pan to prevent sticking.)

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix well and chill before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Add sugar to bananas; beat in egg and water with dissolved soda.
Add flour and salt and mix.
Add melted shortening and stir. Pour into a greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or when tested with toothpick.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onion and squash in small amount of water; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add a few cracker crumbs on top along with 1/2 stick of "pats" of butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal nut bread(bread machine)
directions: Using Welbuilt bread machine, add yeast first, then flour, salt, oatmeal and egg.
Mix water, milk, honey, oil and warm to lukewarm.
Add to machine.
Start on medium setting.
After 10 beeps add chopped nuts and raisins slowly.
You may wish to dust the nuts and raisins with flour so that they will distribute more evenly in the dough.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well. Add pie filling. Batter will be heavy and stiff. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Allow to cool before frosting.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Beat eggs, milk and oil.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together; add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in raisins and/or pecans.
Fold apples in last.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: wacky cake (chocolate)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans or tube pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix together and put in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: savory chicken
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Marinate 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn frequently.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until soft; peel and mash.
Add all other ingredients to potatoes.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole, 9 x 13-inch.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Place chicken in oblong baking dish.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top; spread preserves over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: chicken doritos
directions: Cook chicken day before.
Debone chicken and chop in small pieces.
Chop onion.
Place mushroom soup, chicken soup, Ro-Tel and Velveeta in saucepan and heat until Velveeta is melted.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and flour in heavy pot.
Add eggs, milk, water and vanilla.
Heat until hot (do not boil).
Pour into freezer can and finish filling with whole milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot together.
Turn on high for 30 minutes.

title: chicken italian
directions: Rinse and dry chicken. Dip chicken in Italian salad dressing, then dip in mixture of crumbs, cheese, parsley and salt.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 1 hour.

title: party cookies
directions: Heat
oven
Beat together sugars and shortening. Blend
in
eggs
and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt. Mix well. Stir
in
cup
candies.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.	Press 2 or 3 additional candies into each cookie.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat the margarine, butter and sugar until fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each addition. Add the flour. Add the lemon extract.
Stir in the 7-Up.
Bake in a well-greased mold pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 1/4 hours, depending upon the oven.

title: chicken casserole delight
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth until done. Set aside. Saute onions and celery in butter. Mix chicken, rice, onion, celery, water chestnuts, pimentos, mushrooms, soup and mayonnaise in a 2-quart casserole dish. At this point, casserole can be refrigerated and baked later.

title: marilyn's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well in a microwave safe dish, adding crab meat last so lumps do not get broken. Cover dish and heat approximately 10 minutes in microwave oven. Make sure dip is heated thoroughly. Serve with crackers, tortilla chips or bread pieces.

title: quick cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Layer cherry pie filling on bottom, then pineapple, then sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and pour over the top.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in oven at 325° until golden brown.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix margarine until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spicy roast chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a blender, process all ingredients (except the chicken) until it is a smooth paste.
Rub paste over chicken.
Tie legs together with string and tuck wing tips under back.
Place breast side up in a baking pan.
Roast 1 hour.
Let chicken stand before carving.

title: ruthie's jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into 3 cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Good with Caramel Frosting.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: This is the basic recipe.
At this point 1 (12 ounce) package of chips can be added or batter separated and other ingredients added (date and nut, oatmeal, raisins and coconut)

title: hello dollies
directions: Layer ingredients in baking dish in order given.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Separate from sides of baking dish while cooling.

title: brown rice casserole, italian style
directions: Place uncooked rice on bottom of greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with sausage.
Arrange onions over sausage and sprinkle with garlic salt, oregano and basil.
Pour tomatoes evenly over onions and spices.
Pour water evenly over tomatoes. Sprinkle with cheese and top with green peppers.
