Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until liquid is absorbed.
Uncover and let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
On large baking sheet, stir together pecans and butter.
Bake pecans for 5 to 10 minutes or lightly browned.
Cool pecans on baking sheet for a few minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, salt and peanut butter until smooth.
Sift flour and soda.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls, then press with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: After removing all skin and gristle, cut the fowl into dice and mix it with the celery. Add the salt and pepper and marinate for an hour before using with the oil and vinegar. Mix with mayonnaise dressing and garnish with lettuce, hard-boiled egg and stoned olives or strips of red pepper.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Make 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press thumbprint in each cookie.
Fill with apricot or strawberry preserves.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: mexi bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.
Can serve warm also.
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: baked rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart covered casserole. Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on flour tortilla.
Roll up and chill.
Slice with electric knife.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until it sets.

title: the chewy brownie cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, light brown sugar, water and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded tablespoon 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake one sheet at a time at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until cookies are set.
Cookies will appear soft and moist.
Do not overbake!!
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes.
Remove to sheets of foil on countertop to cool completely.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.

title: glorified egg shortcake
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth; remove from heat.
Slowly stir in milk.
Bring to a boil over direct heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Just before serving, stir in the rest of the ingredients, except biscuits and cheese.
Bring mixture just to a boil.
Serve over biscuits.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Makes 2 generous servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese in order listed.
Pour half the batter into greased deep 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Add remaining batter.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Freeze.
Place in plastic freezer bags until needed.
Bake frozen in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.
A double batch will fill a crock-pot.

title: chippy blond brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in the chocolate chips and pecans. Spread into a
greased 11 x 7 x 2 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: joyce wharton's vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients as listed.
Place in buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rich zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: vicki mckeever's baked cheese
directions: Unroll dough and press together seams to form 12 x 4-inch rectangle.
Place Gouda cheese in center of dough.
Enclose cheese in dough by bringing sides of dough together, pressing edges to seal.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg yolk.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve with assorted crackers and slices of apples.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix chopped apples and sugar; let stand for 1/2 hour.
Add egg, oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and combine with apple mixture.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread rye bread with mustard. Cut into cubes and place bottom of a
buttered
x
x	2-inch baking pan.
Crumble corned beef
evenly
over	bread.	Stir
together sauerkraut, tomato soup,
relish and water; spoon over corned beef.
Bake, uncovered, in	375°
oven
about 25 minutes. Arrange cheese on top; bake 5 minutes more. Serves 8.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage up in small pieces.
Place in pot and add water, enough to cover cabbage. Add butter, salt and pepper. Cook until tender.

title: pasta and vegetables
directions: Prepare vegetables and place in a large container.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain pasta and then mix in with vegetables while hot to soften vegetables.
Add fat-free Italian dressing and chill before serving.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese with wooden spoon until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Drop dough by heaping tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Combine 1/4 cup butter or margarine (melted) and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well and bake in casserole dish for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: bobby q's fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until fudge rises and then settles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; cool and cut up.
Put stuffing in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix broccoli, mayonnaise and cheese together.
Pour over stuffing mix.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Crumble cheese crackers over top and stir.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients: white sugar, brown sugar, butter and peanut butter. Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla. Stir in flour. Shape into balls. Then roll balls in additional granulated sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Take out and immediately press a chocolate kiss into each one. Makes approximately 7 dozen.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown pork chops in butter. Put 2 tbsp. of butter in bottom of pan. Pour rice in the bottom of pan. Put pork chops on top. Pour soup over all. Bake for 1 1/2 hours

title: chicken fajita
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wrap tortillas in aluminum foil.
Place in oven to warm, about 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, in large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add peppers and saute until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove to bowl and keep warm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and milk and add to dry mixture and stir well.
Add melted butter and vanilla and stir well.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir sugar into slightly beaten eggs. Add syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Stir in pecans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: morton's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Dried onion and dried garlic may be used.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with chips, crackers or cornbread.

title: spicy pumpkin cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add pumpkin and milk, then remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased and floured loaf pan, 9 x 13-inch.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread into bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Mix in mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve chilled.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Stuff into pockets of chops; secure openings with wooden picks.
Sprinkle chops with salt; dredge in seasoned dry bread crumbs.
Place chops in lightly greased baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup pineapple juice over chops.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add remaining juice; bake 30 more minutes.

title: seasoning salt
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in an airtight container.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef together, stirring until crumbly. Drain well.
Add cheese and mushrooms.
Put a lid on your skillet until cheese melts.
Stir and spread on bread.
Put on a cookie sheet and put under the broiler until it bubbles, watch carefully not to burn.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Mix cocoa in coloring and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla, flour and salt alternately with buttermilk to mixture, fold in vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Put raisins into saucepan and cover with 2 or 3 cups of water. Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together 4 cups flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In a separate bowl, mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla mixture with drained raisins.
Add 1 cup water raisins were cooked in to mixture alternately with flour mixture, stirring by hand.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: best of west dip
directions: Cook bacon and crumble.
Mix together all ingredients and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
Eat with nacho chips.

title: texas beef enchilada
directions: Butter a 9 x 2 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a skillet cook beef and add chili powder and chillies. Combine undiluted soups and enchilada sauce in a saucepan, stirring until well blended.
Add 1 1/2 cups of soup mixture to beef.
Layer 4 tortillas out flat in bottom of casserole, overlapping if necessary.
Spread beef mixture over tortillas. Continue layering with the 4 remaining tortillas, then top with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes or until bubbly and light brown.

title: zesty vegetable pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Line a large salad bowl with salad greens.

In a separate container, mix pasta, tomatoes, broccoli, onion, green pepper, carrots and red cabbage. Pour in approximately 1/4 cup of creamy Italian dressing, followed by the light Italian dressing to desired taste; toss.
Put mixture in salad bowl, sprinkle with McCormick Salad Supreme seasoning. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except peanut butter chips.
Pour half of the mixture into greased and floured Bundt pan. Sprinkle with 2/3 cup peanut butter chips.
Pour remaining batter and top with remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pennsylvania dutch pepper relish
directions: Combine all vegetables in food processor; chop very fine. Transfer to a large mixing bowl; stir in salt.
Let mixture stand at room temperature for 1 hour; drain vegetables.
Stir in sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Store in airtight containers in refrigerator.
Makes 10 cups.

title: mom's double french toast
directions: Cut bread into 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices and set aside.
Combine milk and beaten eggs and pour into a 10 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Place bread slices on top, saturate and then turn over, making sure bread absorbs milk.

title: zucchini pie(a crustless quiche)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl until the zucchini is coated.
Pour into a 12-inch buttered pie plate or oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden. Serves 6 to 8 and is equally good hot as it is room temperature.

title: heavenly hash popcorn
directions: Spread popcorn on buttered jelly roll pan or baking sheet. Sprinkle with the marshmallows and peanuts.
Arrange chocolate bars on top.
Place in preheated 300° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly, then toss.
Makes 2 1/2-quarts.
For gift giving, pack in airtight container.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cut margarine into the flour until blended well.
Add poppy seed and Cheddar cheese.
Add water tablespoon by tablespoon until a ball can be formed.
Knead dough until smooth.
Roll out dough and place in pie plate.
Pinch edges and prick inside with a fork.

title: lemonade cookies(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add 3 ounces lemonade.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Place hash brown potatoes in greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Add cooked hamburger over the top. Sprinkle with the salt and pepper. Spread 8 ounces of shredded cheese over the top. Add the two cans of potato soup, that have been mixed well. Spread the remaining 8 ounces of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: ultimate spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate. Stir before serving.

title: catfish chowder
directions: Saute
pork in large skillet until lightly browned, add onions and
cook until just tender.
Stir in drained catfish, potatoes, water (or fish broth) and salt.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes, stirring
occasionally.
Stir in milk and evaporated milk;
heat until
just
hot.
Do not boil!
Serves 10 hearty appetites or 20 average appetites.

title: the house hermit
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and oil.
Mix milk and molasses.
Add to dry mixture.
Fold in raisins.
Grease cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a medium casserole. Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes or until set.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Shred zucchini, onions and salt.
Combine 3 ingredients and let set overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine the rest of ingredients, boil 3 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: impossible pie(forms its own crust)
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender for one minute.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg before placing in oven.
Bake at 350° for forty-five minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Put Doritos over top; sprinkle cheese and milk over top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cinnamon rolls (or pull-aparts)
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan. Mix brown sugar and pudding mix.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over brown sugar-pudding mixture.
Spread pecans over this.
Pour melted butter over pecans.
Place on cabinet or countertop overnight.
Do not cover.

title: cranberry-ginger sauce
directions: Combine cranberries, 3/4 cup water, sugar, grated orange peel and ground ginger in heavy medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Cook until cranberry skins burst, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes later, transfer sauce to a processor.
Add maple syrup and process until almost smooth.
Stir in chopped crystallized ginger. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: ms. ida's coconut pie
directions: Mix granulated sugar and flour.
Beat egg yolks, milk, vanilla and butter; mix with sugar and flour.
Cook double boiler style until thick.
Add coconut and pour into 9-inch pie shell.

title: no flour cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and drop on cookie sheet, press with a fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Beat egg with a small amount of water.
Take chicken cutlet and dip in egg mixture, then cover with bread crumbs.
Take a flat tray and grease with oil.
Place chicken on tray and drip small amounts of oil over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on each side. Serve with lemon juice to drip over chicken.

title: coffee-orange fudge cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
In large mixer bowl combine cake mix, sour cream, oil, water, eggs, pudding mix, liqueur, orange rind and cinnamon.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed until well blended, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate pieces and pour into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 or 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for ten minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar just before serving.
Makes 12 to 16 servings. Freezes well.

title: jim's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute butter, onions and garlic until onions are clear.
Add peppers and pepper juice.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add the rest of ingredients and cook on low for an hour or so.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon in large bowl.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar to make dressing.
Beat until creamy.
Pour over broccoli mixture and chill.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Melt butter and cream sugar and dash of salt.
Add milk, nuts and coconut.
Form in soft balls and freeze.
(Refrigerate overnight.)
Will be easier to make balls.

title: pumpkin bars(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
With electric mixer, combine margarine, apple juice concentrate, fructose and mashed banana.
Beat in egg, pumpkin and vanilla.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in bowl in order given.
Put into 2 loaf pans, small size (7 3/4 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave boneless breast au gratin
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in a shallow baking dish and sprinkle with combined sherry and broth.
Cover with combined sherry and broth.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook in microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Turn chicken and cook another 8 minutes.

title: michigan apple pie
directions: Line a deep 10-inch pie plate with pastry.
Put apple mixture in pastry and bake at 360° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate-covered cherry cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, beat together oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients; beat until well blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down center of dough with thumb.
Drain maraschino cherries, reserving juice.
Place a cherry in the center of each cookie.

title: chocolate or lemon lush cake
directions: Mix
first
ingredients.
Spread
in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake
at
about
minutes or until light brown. Cool completely.
Cream the cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar. Spread on	crust.	Mix instant pudding with milk.	Beat until thick. Spread on preceding.
Top
with
remaining	Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut; cut in squares.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix together graham crackers (crumbled), sugar and melted butter.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat gently.
Bake at 400° about 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill about 1 hour.
Form a ball and roll into pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage and cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread bread pieces on bottom. Sprinkle crumbled, browned sausage over bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sausage.
Beat 6 eggs with 2 1/2 cups milk and pour over mixture.
Spread 1 can cream of mushroom soup over top.
Bake at 350° uncovered 30 to 45 minutes.

title: autumn apple bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Sift in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture, alternating with apples.
Stir in lemon rind and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.
Cool before slicing.

title: just cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done in a 17 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch cookie sheet with sides.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Melt marshmallows with juice of strawberries and pineapple in a double boiler.
Cool.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and chopped pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in freezer in glass casserole dish.
Cut into squares before serving.

title: banana chip muffins
directions: Combine in bowl all ingredients and mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour batter into greased or paper-lined muffin cups.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Check often.

title: 4 can chocolate cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients except flour.
Fold in the flour. Use the Hershey's chocolate syrup can to do all the measuring. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Put 1 can chocolate filling over cake while warm enough to melt slightly. Add chopped pecans, if desired.

title: golden shrimp puff
directions: Remove crusts; quarter bread.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings. Layer 1/2 bread on bottom, then shrimp, cheese and remaining bread.
Pour liquid over all.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Use a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Can let stand in refrigerator up to 24 hours before baking.

title: toffee nut bars
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening and sugar.
Stir in flour. Press and flatten with hand to cover bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Then spread with the following Almond Coconut Topping.

title: squeeze play
directions: Serve in Collins glass.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together pie filling, milk, pineapple, coconut and pecans. Add 1 container Cool Whip and pour into mold.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: bacon delight
directions: Put tomatoes through a sieve.
Heat puree in double boiler. Add cornstarch to thicken, stirring frequently.
Add seasonings. Arrange slices of bread in shallow baking dish.
Cover with cheese, then with tomato mixture.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 400° until bacon is crisp.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into a loaf.
This can be baked in the oven at 350° or fixed in a crock-pot.

title: honey nutters
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey and milk in a large bowl and stir until blended.
Crush graham crackers between wax paper to make fine crumbs.
Add crumbs to peanut butter mixture; mix with hands until well blended.
Pour wheat germ onto plate.
Make little balls and roll in wheat germ.
Eat.
Makes 82.

title: butter biscuits for coffee
directions: Prepare:
Sift flour with baking powder.
Beat butter on high speed until fluffy (15 to 20 minutes).
Add sugar and continue beating for another 15 to 20 minutes.
Beat eggs; add vanilla. Pour into batter mixture.
Add flour, little by little, then by hand work the mixture.
Add almonds.
(Dough will be soft.)
Shape into cookie shapes.
Put in buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: paska-babka
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and let stand while preparing other ingredients.
In a large bowl, mix eggs and sugar. Add melted butter, oil, milk and the yeast mixture.
Add flour gradually and mix either by hand or mixer with dough hook.
Put dough into a larger greased container, cover with dish towel and let it rise in warm, draftfree area until double in size.
Then, grease pans with Crisco and gently put the dough in about 1/3 high. Pat evenly and let rise again.
When almost full, baste with slightly beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, then lower temperature to 325° for another 30 minutes or until nice and golden.
Bake in coffee cans; do not use wide round pans.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling and pineapple in oblong baking pan.
Mix together evenly.
Dump cake mix over the top of mixture; do not mix together.
Pour melted butter over top of cake mix until it is covered with liquid.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top should be brown and bubbly.
The cake will look like a cobbler.
Serve warm with ice cream for a delicious delite!

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl.
Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars. Add eggs one at a time.
Beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture. Roll into 1 1/2 balls and place 3 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375 for 10 - 15 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: herbed oyster crackers
directions: Mix herbs and oil. Drizzle over crackers.
Stir well.
Store in airtight container for 24 hours.
Serve on salads, soup or as hors d'oeuvres.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Heat oil in a deep fryer at least 2 inches deep.
Cut off pepper stems and remove seeds and core.
Stuff peppers with cream cheese.
Roll out biscuits on floured pie sheet.
Wrap stuffed pepper with 1/2 slice American cheese.
Wrap with biscuit.
Drop into hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Place sugar, flour and salt in double boiler.
Add milk.
Stir over heat until thickened, like pudding.
Add egg yolks; cook 3 to 4 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites on high speed until they form stiff peaks.
Gradually add sugar and cream of tartar while beating.
Spread meringue over pie; sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° until peaks and coconut brown.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in a 2-quart glass bowl; add butter.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add water or milk, stirring until blended.
Microwave on High for 1 minute. Stir in mini marshmallows and vanilla, using wire whisk.

title: cocoa bavarian cream
directions: Sprinkle gelatin into 1 1/2 cups cold milk in medium saucepan. Let stand 3 to 4 minutes to soften.
Combine sugar and cocoa. Add to gelatin mixture in saucepan.
Add corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat; stir in butter until melted.
Blend in 1 3/4 cups of milk and the vanilla.
Pour into large mixer bowl.
Cool and chill until almost set.

title: swiss steaks
directions: Cut steaks into serving sizes, flour and brown.
Place in roasting pan.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Add bell pepper, if desired.
Cook, uncovered, at 250° until meat is very tender, about 45 minutes, the longer it is cooked the better.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Top with another 3/4 cup pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Fry onions and garlic slowly in oil until tender.
Add meat and brown quickly.
Add green pepper, then other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into large, greased casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 250° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until almost firm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Blend in pie filling and crushed pineapple, drained.
Chill until firm.

title: zucchini-tomato italienne
directions: In large skillet, heat olive oil.
Add garlic and onion and cook about 4 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook about 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomatoes, basil, oregano and pepper (to taste) and cook until zucchini is soft (about 10 minutes).
Turn off heat.
Add about 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
If very watery, stir to thicken.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Drain pineapple; keep juice.
Add enough boiling water to juice to make 1 cup liquid.
Dissolve jello in boiling mix.
Add to melted ice cream and nuts.
Chill in refrigerator.
Garnish with cherries.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend.

title: out of this world rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Let stand 10 minutes. Combine dissolved yeast, eggs, 2 1/2 cups flour, 1 cup warm water, shortening, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth. Add remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Cover; let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and refrigerate overnight.
Three hours before baking, roll out as desired.
For dinner rolls, divide dough in half.
Roll each half into a 1/2-inch thick rectangle.
Spread with soft butter.
Starting with long side, roll up jelly-roll style.
Cut in 1-inch slices.
Place in greased muffin tins.
Rub tops lightly with soft butter.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Make 2 dozen rolls.

title: auntie's icebox cookies
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and lemon extract; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Divide dough into 4 parts and shape into 1 1/2 x 11-inch rolls.
Wrap in foil and chill overnight.
Slice cookies 3/8-inch thick.
Bake on greased sheets at 350° for about 10 minutes. Yields about 17 dozen cookies.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion six minutes on High in microwave, using Tupperware colander.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add other ingredients and heat 3 to 4 minutes more.
Serve with warm nacho chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box until set.
Then add all ingredients and mix well; chill at least an hour.
Use large bowl. Great for the holidays.
You can use strawberry Jell-O for Christmas and orange for Thanksgiving.

title: snowed - under meat loaf
directions: Mix well 1/4 cup gravy with all ingredients except potatoes; shape firmly into loaf; place in shallow baking pan.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: In mixing bowl stir flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, bananas, oil, undrained pineapple and vanilla and add all at once to the dry ingredients.
Stir until well moistened.
Pour into tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli and cauliflower into small bites.
Mix together with English peas.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Place a layer of broccoli, cauliflower, peas, grated cheese and bacon bits.
Cover this with dressing mix.
Make layers until all ingredients are used.

title: summer crab cakes
directions: Mix mayonnaise and seasoning in medium bowl.
Add crabmeat, 1/3 cup cracker crumbs, green onions and bell pepper.
Mix carefully to avoid breaking up crabmeat.
Form mixture into four (1/2-inch thick) patties.
Place remaining 1/3 cup cracker crumbs in shallow bowl.
Press crab cakes into crumbs, coating completely.
(Can be prepared 3 hours ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.)
Heat oil in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Fry cakes until brown.

title: low-fat mexican dip
directions: Add salsa to cream cheese.
Blend with mixer.

title: tuna chowder
directions: Combine celery soup and stewed tomatoes in a 1 3/4 quart saucepan.
Add onion and tuna.
Heat to serving temperature over medium heat.
May be topped with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: upside-down cornbread
directions: Cook hamburger meat until well done.
Drain off grease.
(In another pan, cook onions and bell pepper.)
When done, mix salt, pepper, cheese, flour and tomato paste.
After you have all this mixed, put in a long dish, mix corn.
Mix together and spread on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: green beans almondine
directions: Place green beans in a small non-metal bowl. Sprinkle with water. Micro-cook, covered, on 100% power for 3 to 4 minutes or just until tender. Let stand, covered, while preparing butter mixture.

title: blueberry cake coffee ring
directions: Combine flour, baking
powder
and
salt.
Cream sugar, shortening and egg, using milk and berries last.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add milk and well-beaten egg.
Mix well.
Peel and core apples, then cut into sections.
Dip each piece into batter and fry in deep hot fat until brown.
Dry on unglazed paper and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pork barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients about 15 minutes and strain.
Cook 20 pounds of pork loin ribs over charcoal pit.
Baste and turn every few minutes.
Takes 2 to 3 hours.
Ribs should be dark and crusty on outside.
Taste to check if done.
May also be used on pork shoulders.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In large bowl, combine sauerkraut, green pepper, celery, onion, carrot, sugar, corn, oil, vinegar, salt and pimentos.
Mix lightly.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, pancake syrup, chopped nuts and cinnamon in a layer cake pan.
Top with refrigerator biscuits and bake as biscuit package directed or until golden brown.

title: jacob's favorite
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain; add cooked elbow macaroni, corn and tomato paste.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Mix and drop in baking pan.
Bake in hot oven between 350° and 400° (I use 375°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
